title: baked chimichangas
directions: *I substitute an equal amount of boiled, chopped chicken for the pork.

title: spicy shrimp spread
directions: Blend all ingredients together until very well blended.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Mound on pretty serving dish. Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Have at room temperature to serve, otherwise keep refrigerated.
Serve as spread on crackers or rye bread.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Layer 1/3 of meat in bottom of loaf pan.
Put 1/2 of cheese over meat.
Layer another 1/3 of meat. Cover with remaining cheese.
Top all with last 1/3 of meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco oil and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time. Cream well after each addition.
Stir dry ingredients and add to mixture, mixing well.
Bake in a well greased pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: my ham hawaiian
directions: Melt butter (1/2) and add green peppers and ham and cook for 5 minutes.
Drain pineapple.
Keep liquid, cut up in bite size pieces.
Mix liquid and next 6 ingredients.
Stir into ham mixture and cook until thick.
Add pineapple and heat.
Prepare rice adding remaining butter and cloves after rice has warmed a few minutes. Serve with ham.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in a large kettle; then drain.
In a large skillet cook ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Simmer.
Pour ground beef, onions, bell pepper and Manwich over drained spaghetti.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Sprinkle diced strawberries with enough sugar to sweeten (3 tablespoons, maybe) and set aside.
Mix in a pan and cook vinegar, food coloring, salt, sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Add berries and pour in a cooked pie crust.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: raspberry (or strawberry) pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together, and add to berries. Line 9 inch pie pan with pastry.
Add filling, dot with butter. Cover with top crust.
Bake in very hot oven 450° for ten minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into slices.
Mix all ingredients and put in casserole sprayed with Pam.
Pour 1/4 cup milk over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Stir once while baking.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine meat, rice, soups and 1 cup grated cheese.
Mix and place in baking dish and sprinkle remaining of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tacos delight supreme
directions: Brown hamburger meat; add taco seasoning.
Stir until mixed well.
Next, cut up lettuce and tomatoes.
Next, put hamburger into taco.
Place your cheeses into taco and place into oven at 250°.
Last, place lettuce and tomatoes onto taco and add more cheese if you like, then add your sour cream.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients together and pour in two 9-inch floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in small skillet; add eggs and cook, stirring constantly until firm, but still moist.
Set aside.
Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
In skillet, crumble bacon and set aside.
Add next 4 ingredients to drippings; cook until onions are tender.
Stir in rice, soy sauce, eggs and bacon.
Cook until thoroughly heated. Yield:
6 servings.

title: potato rolls
directions: Cream the hot mashed potatoes, sugar and salt.
Add yeast mixture and eggs. Add flour to make stiff dough.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and refrigerate.
Make out rolls the next morning.
Let rise again; allow at least 1 1/2 hours to rise. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: alabama fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil (a rolling boil), stirring continually.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and beat until fudge holds its shape.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour on wax paper. Cut when cool.

title: beef and cabbage rolls in sauerkraut
directions: Combine ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bury cabbage beef rolls in this mixture.
Cook on low heat 4 to 5 hours.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water, vinegar and salt on high heat until it spins a thread.
Start eggs to beating when thread spins and beat real stiff.
Pour over beaten eggs while still beating.
Add vanilla and nuts after candy begins to thicken.
Drop on wax paper and cool.

title: betty's cracker delight
directions: Crush crackers.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar while beating.
Fold in crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool overnight.
Use Cool Whip on top.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion and celery for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with noodles.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Allow to set 10 to 15 minutes.

title: venison roast
directions: Rub roast with liberal amount of salt and red pepper.
Mix onions and garlic; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Use most of onions and garlic to stuff roast.
Place roast in roasting pan. Pour Italian dressing over roast.
Place green onions and remainder of onions and garlic on top of roast.
Place bacon strips on top of roast.
Cover roasting pan and marinate overnight.

title: peanut clusters(candy)
directions: Microwave chocolate chips and Reese's peanut butter chips on High for 2 minutes. Stir with metal spoon. Pour salted Spanish peanuts into chips and blend together. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: peach cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Mix just until blended.
Stir in peaches and pecans.
Spoon batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pina colada salad(diabetic)
directions: Combine oranges, pineapple and banana in medium bowl.
Whip low calorie topping with 1/2 cup fruit liquid (all of pineapple juice and enough orange liquid to make 1/2 cup).
Whip in vanilla and rum extracts.
Fold into fruit mixture; sprinkle with coconut.
Chill several hours before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: creole style green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Add onion and green pepper to 3 tablespoons bacon drippings; cook until tender. Blend in flour, sugar and seasonings.
Add tomatoes; cook until thickened.
Add beans; heat thoroughly.
Garnish with bacon. Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil oleo and sugar together in saucepan for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add cream; boil 1 more minute.
Let cool.
Add vanilla and enough powdered sugar to thicken.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onions in baking dish.
Prepare gravy according to package directions.
Pour over potatoes and onions. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until tender.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; do not peel.
Cut in thin slices.
Peel and wash onions.
Combine onions and cucumbers.
Add salt and let stand 2 hours.
Drain.
Heat vinegar, water, celery seed, mustard seed, sugar, ginger and turmeric to boiling.
Add cucumbers and onions; boil slowly until tender.
Pack in freshly sterilized jars while hot.
Makes 5 pints.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time and continue beating while adding salt and vanilla.
Slowly mix in the flour.
Mix very well and pour into greased tube cake pan.
(Note:
Grease bottom of pan and cut waxed paper to fit bottom.
Helps get the cake out without breaking edges.)
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until tester comes out clean.
Cool before removing from the pan.

title: pistachio nut swirl cake
directions: Combine cake mix, instant pudding, eggs, sour cream, oil and almond extract in large mixing bowl; blend.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour 1/2 cake batter into greased and floured tube pan; sprinkle with half of sugar mixture.
Repeat layers; top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until test shows done.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: vegetable lo mein
directions: Cut the onion into 12 wedges.
Julienne the carrots and pepper.
Cut the broccoli into bite size pieces.
Heat a large wok, then add peanut oil.
Add onion and stir-fry until it is slightly tender and beginning to brown, about 2 minutes.
Add carrots, pepper, broccoli and garlic and continue to stir-fry for about 2 minutes.

title: beer wieners
directions: Cut up wieners.
Mix barbecue sauce, beer and brown sugar. Pour over wieners.
Let set overnight, then heat in crock-pot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir mayonnaise, sour cream, spinach, soup mix, water chestnuts and onions together.
Cover and put in refrigerator to chill.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese in a bowl and mix well.
Place on a greased 10 1/2 x 15-inch baking sheet.
Spread spaghetti sauce on top.
Top with pepperoni, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: coconut crunch torte
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, coconut and pecans.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Add vanilla extract and salt.
Beat until mixed; gradually add sugar and continue beating until egg whites form stiff peaks.
Fold in graham cracker mixture.
Spread into well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 8 pieces and serve with whipped cream and strawberries.

title: turkish chicken
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft and add tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Place chicken in roaster and pour the onion mixture over the
top.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: potato tart
directions: Put cubed Polish sausage in bottom of pie shells.
Mix all other ingredients together.
(Save 1 cup shredded cheese.) Pour over Polish sausage.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until set.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: steak and mushroom sauce
directions: Put round steak in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put sliced onion on top of steak. Pour cream of mushroom soup over that.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook meat in deep skillet or Dutch oven until all red has disappeared.
Cook chopped onions in separate skillet in a little butter or margarine.
Add all ingredients to beef and cook on medium heat for about 2 hours.
If too thick, add a little water while cooking.

title: baby squash
directions: Combine cheese and garlic.
Wash vegetables and roll wet vegetables in cheese/garlic/salt mixture.
Place on a cookie sheet that has been lightly sprayed with Pam and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

(I broil for 5 to 10 minutes until a light golden brown). Can substitute 2 small squash and 2 small zucchini for baby yellow squash and zucchini; cut each into quarters and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Put in layers as listed. Seal tightly overnight. Toss with fork before serving.

title: sausage and sweet potatoes
directions: Shape sausage meat into small patties and brown lightly on both sides (or links lightly browned).
Slice sweet potatoes into 3/4-inch thick rounds and arrange in a baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Place sausage on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter, cream cheese, powdered sugar; slowly add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze.

title: cranberry chicken and stuffing
directions: Place chicken quarters in shallow baking pan. On piece of foil large enough to cover the pan, rub a tablespoon of margarine and sprinkle with 1/2 of soup mix.

Rub chicken with another tablespoon of margarine and sprinkle with remaining soup mix. Drain liquid from cranberry sauce and drizzle over chicken. Reserve 1 cup of cranberry sauce and spread remaining cranberry sauce over chicken.
Cover with prepared foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
In large bowl, mix together hot water, seasoning packet from stuffing and remaining 2 tablespoons margarine, stirring until margarine melts.
Stir in stuffing crumbs until moistened; mix in 1 cup cranberry sauce.
Remove foil from pan and reserve.
Push chicken aside and add stuffing mix in 4 mounds. Drizzle pan drippings over stuffing.
Sprinkle chicken with celery salt, pepper and almonds.
Bake, uncovered, about 20 minutes, until a fork inserts easily.
Remove browned soup mix from foil and sprinkle over chicken and dressing.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cheese-dried beef on toast for two
directions: Place soup (undiluted) in small, heavy-bottomed saucepan. Heat over low heat until hot.
Stir while heating.
Cut across the roll of dried beef 3 or 4 times.
Add beef to soup.
Stir over low heat.
Toast bread and place on two plates.
Spoon cheese-beef mixture over toast.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Melt butter and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Place 8 pineapple rings over brown sugar.
Put a cherry in center of each ring.
Pour cake batter in pan carefully.
Bake at 350° for 48 minutes or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Add soda and vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Shred enough potatoes to measure 4 cups; drain.
Mix potatoes, eggs, onion, flour and salt.
Heat 2 tablespoons of the bacon fat in 12-inch skillet over medium heat until hot.
Pour in about 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Flatten each with spatula into pancake about 4 inches in diameter.
Cook pancakes until golden brown, about 2 minutes on each side.
Keep warm.
Repeat with remaining batter.
(Add remaining bacon fat as needed to prevent sticking.)
Makes 16 pancakes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients except Crisco oil for frying in medium mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Let stand 1 hour.
Heat 2 to 3 inches Crisco oil in deep fryer or large saucepan to 350°.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls into hot Crisco oil.
Fry, a few at a time, 5 to 6 minutes, or until deep golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Repeat with remaining batter.
Serve immediately or keep warm in 175° oven.
Makes 14 to 16 fritters.

title: baked ham steak
directions: Place first 4 ingredients into roast pan using raisins to fill apples.
Sprinkle on sugar; pour juice over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes if ham is parboiled and 2 hours if not. Use a cover during first 30 minutes of baking time.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef goulash
directions: Brown meat in skillet, making sure to brown on all sides and not to crowd pan. Meat should not touch other meat. Place in slow cooker. Place onion in skillet and cook until translucent. Add garlic and cook until fragrant. Place in slow cooker. Add stock to skillet and scrape up brown pieces. Take 2 3/4 cups of the stock and put in slow cooker. Add flour to remaining stock and whisk until thickened. Add to slow cooker. Add remaining ingredients, except for sour cream and parsley leaves, and stir. Set slow cooker for desired time. Serve with buttered egg noodles, preferably wide. Garnish with sour cream and parsley.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Open rolls out flat and bake on 2 cookie sheets and cool. Beat with a beater the sour cream, cream cheese and Ranch dressing. Spread mixture on top of baked rolls and add vegetables and cheese.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: *If cherries are used, then add 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.

title: quick pecan rolls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in an 8-inch cake pan.
Top with biscuits.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Cool 5 minutes and invert onto plate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream lard, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and chill.
Roll into small balls with hands and place on cookie sheet.
Indent each cookie with fork tines, both horizontal and vertical.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a roasting pan 3 times to coat with oil.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs, beating mixture after each egg.
Gradually add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well. Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake in greased pan at 350° 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef in fine pieces.
Add beans.	Mix well.
Add sugar, mustard and ketchup.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Place bacon slices on top of mixture.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done in a tube pan.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream together. Mix poppy seed, crackers and melted butter in another bowl. Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Put 1/2 chicken in bottom.
Top with part of soup mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed mixture. Repeat layering.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup and margarine; stir in pecans. Pour into pie shell and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until brown and spongy.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and add Ro-Tel and cream of chicken soup. Stir all together.
In casserole bowl, put 1 layer of hamburger mixtures, then a layer of corn tortillas, then a layer of Velveeta cheese.
Keep making layers until all of meat mixture is used. Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: triple chocolate pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square pan.
In medium bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar and cocoa.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk, margarine, 1/4 cup topping and vanilla until blended. Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips. Spread evenly in prepared pan.
In a small bowl, combine remaining 1/4 cup milk, remaining 1/2 cup topping and hot water.
Pour liquid mixture carefully over top of mixture in pan.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup chips over surface.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes. Spoon into dishes and top with whipped topping. Very rich.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Mix eggs, salt, half and half and mustard.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan:
bread slices, sausage, cheese and egg mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage and cheese which has been grated.
Mix well. Add Bisquick, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well with hands.
Roll into balls, one teaspoon each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven 25 minutes.
Can be frozen.
Reheat in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian carrots
directions: Cook carrots 15 minutes, then add green pepper and cook 3 minutes longer.
Drain.
Drain pineapple, reserving liquid to make 1/3 cup and pour into saucepan.
In saucepan, combine rest of ingredients and cook until bubbly.
Pour over carrots and pineapple and heat through.
Serves 6.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Heat over medium heat sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Heat until it starts to boil; remove from heat and let cool 1 minute. Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Add oatmeal, stirring until coated.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper. Refrigerate until firm.

title: party dip
directions: Blend together with mixer.
Good with fresh vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese with the electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with pizza sauce, Mozzarella cheese, remaining 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and peppers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve with assorted Nabisco crackers or Stella D'Oro breadsticks.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut cooked chicken into large pieces.
Combine with carrots, onion, salad dressing and mustard.
This should be done one day in advance of serving.
Refrigerate.

title: spanish potato and ham omelet
directions: Slice potatoes, onions and ham with thinnest slicing disc of food processor. (If you don't have food processor, slice as thinly as possible by hand.)

title: nut crisp cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream first 4 ingredients.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir into creamed ingredients.
Mix in chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a moderate oven (350°).

title: "hamburger cone-pone pie"
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients. In a separate bowl, mix up cornbread, following package directions. Spray casserole dish with no-stick cooking spray. Pour in meat mixture. Pour cornbread mix on top of that. Bake according to cornbread package. Serves 4 to 5 adults. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Mix broccoli and onion in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients, except cheese, for 1 minute with mixer or 15 seconds in blender.
Pour into pie plate and top with cheese.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in middle comes out clean (35 to 40 minutes).
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: almond cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve warm with crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, oleo and sugars. Add eggs, separately. Beat well. Add remaining ingredients in order given. Drop from spoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat with salt.
Drain off excess fat.
Add jar of picante sauce and mix well.
Then add cream cheese and mix well until well heated.
Reduce heat and let simmer for about 5 minutes.
It's great with tortilla chips.

title: streusel top fruit pie
directions: Makes 9-inch pie. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Combine ingredients to form a soft pastry dough.
Press pastry evenly in 9-inch pie pan. Flute if desired.

title: super dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Spread in two (8-inch) pie pans (1/2 in each pan).
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable delight
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: shawarma (lamb pitas)
directions: Trim fat from lamb. Combine 2 cups onion and next 6 ingredients in a large zip-top plastic bag. Add lamb to bag and seal. Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours, turning occasionally. Remove lamb from bag and discard marinade. Place lamb on a broiler pan. Insert meat thermometer in thickest portion of lamb. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until thermometer registers 145° (medium rare) to 160° (medium). Let stand for 15 minutes and then slice lengthwise into thin strips. Spread each pita with about 2 1/2 Tbsp. Yogurt-Tahini Dip. Divide lamb, red onion, mint, tomato and pickles evenly among each pita and roll up. Serve immediately.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain peaches and cut into thirds.
Add hot noodles to the margarine, so it will melt.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Put into casserole and bake at 350° for an hour and a half.
Cover with crushed corn flakes, if desired.

title: cold eggplant(appetizer)
directions: Saute eggplant in 1/2 cup of oil for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add garlic, celery and green pepper (and more oil if needed).
Saute until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add tomato sauce, seasonings, vinegar and parsley.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 10 more minutes.
Refrigerate a minimum of 48 hours or up to 1 week.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: In skillet or big stew pot, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add chicken and cook until browned.
Add soup, 1/2 cup water and vegetable combo.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Serves 4.

title: cheddar cheese spaghetti
directions: Fry ground beef.
Cut and dice onion, bell pepper and mushrooms.
Drain ground beef and add vegetables.
Add noodles to boiling water and add 1 teaspoon of salt.
When noodles are done, drain and add mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese soup, tomato soup and tomato paste.
Mix well and serve with garlic bread.

title: rice(risotto)
directions: In a large saucepan, dilute tomato paste in the chicken broth. Bring to a boil, then lower heat just to keep warm.
In a heavy pan or skillet, melt oleo and saute onion lightly.
Add rice, stirring to soak in oleo.
Add broth with a ladle, enough to cover rice and stir until broth is absorbed over medium heat, stirring. Repeat until all broth is used.
It cooks in about 30 to 40 minutes.
Spoon out on a platter or large bowl, sprinkling Italian grated cheese in between layers.
Serve hot.

title: sparkling mint punch
directions: Sprinkle sugar overnight and cover with hot water.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Strain and chill.
Also chill juices and carbonated beverages.
When ready to serve, combine mint, syrup and juices.
Pour over ice ring in punch bowl, then slowly pour carbonated beverage over ring and serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Put crescent rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing; spread on crust.
Put vegetables on top.
Cover and chill.

title: apple-cocoa cake
directions: *Use any flavored chips for variation.

title: pork chili verde
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan over medium heat, combine pork, 1/2 cup broth and garlic. Cover; cook 30 minutes.

Remove lid; cook, stirring often, until liquid caramelizes and meat browns, about 20 minutes. Add remaining broth; scrape brown bits from bottom of pan. Add tomatoes with juice, green chilies, onion and oregano. Cover and simmer gently,

stirring occasionally, until meat pulls apart easily, about 1 1/2 hours. Serve with warm flour tortillas or over rice with lime wedges to squeeze over meat mixture, if desired. Makes about 10 cups; 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg-cheese puff
directions: Beat eggs; add salt, pepper and milk.
Cut crust from bread; butter one side.
Butter a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Place 6 slices of bread (buttered side down) in the dish.
Cover with grated cheese and ham.
Place remaining slices of bread (buttered side up) on top.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered, in pan of water.

title: plain muffins
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Beat up eggs.
Add milk and melted shortening to eggs.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ones. Stir just enough to blend.
Fill lightly greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: our favorite meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix beef, celery, onions, eggs, horseradish, salt and 1/4 cup chili sauce.
Shape into three loaves; place on rack in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes. Mix mustard and 1/2 cup chili sauce in a bowl; spread over loaves.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Garnish with parsley.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt margarine in skillet. Whisk in the flour. Keep stirring until margarine is all soaked into flour. Slowly add milk, whisking as you pour. Stir and simmer until creamy and thickened. Add salt and pepper to taste. Stir in chicken and juice. Heat thoroughly and serve over toast.

title: easy sausage pizza
directions: Mix together Bisquick and water; spread on pizza pan.
Add spaghetti sauce over dough.
Top with onion, green pepper, olives, mushrooms and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: slush
directions: Mix all together and freeze overnight.
When ready to use, fill glass half full of slush and fill rest of glass with chilled Squirt.
Add a straw for ease in drinking.
Be careful ... it may creep up on you!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil
chicken
until
tender.
Mix chicken with chicken broth and pour
in
a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish sprayed with Pam. Spread sour
cream over chicken; add saltine crackers.
Sprinkle poppy seed over crackers.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Leave lid off if possible.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage in 2 cups water.
Dice bacon; fry until crisp. When cabbage is done (do not drain water); add bacon.
In the bacon drippings, brown flour, then add the cabbage; stir in vinegar.
Mix and boil about 5 minutes longer.

title: spicy zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
In a large mixing bowl, blend all ingredients except nuts and coconut. Beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 55 to 60 minutes, then turn out on wire rack to cool. Glaze.

title: clay's chicken delight
directions: Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour this over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning chicken once. Serves 8.

title: chicken and corkscrew macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni.
Cut up tomatoes in a large saucepan or 10-inch skillet.
Stir together undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, green pepper, drained canned chicken and macaroni.
Mix together and add cheese. Cook together for about 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Shred bread and knead all ingredients together.
Form meat loaf.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, onion salt and garlic salt. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and milk.
Add butter or oleo to mashed sweet potatoes and blend with the milk and egg mixture.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: korean deep fried egg rolls(twigim man du)
directions: Using no oil, fry beef and pork.
Briefly cook cabbage in boiling water; drain very well and add to meat mixture.
Rinse, drain and chop bean sprouts.
Combine all vegetables and seasoning ingredients.
Brush each wonton skin with beaten egg.
Center 1 tablespoon filling and fold diagonally into triangle shape, forcing out air and pinch-sealing completely to form dumplings. Deep-fry in 375° oil, until just golden.
Makes 50.

title: russian salad
directions: Put Jell-O in saucepan with can of pineapple and juice and cream cheese, softened.
Bring to boil and cook one minute.
Let cool and refrigerate.
Beat whip cream; add sugar to taste. Refrigerate.
When Jell-O starts to congeal, mix whip cream, nuts and Jell-O together; leave overnight in refrigerator.

title: quick barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet. Drain off liquids. Stir in remaining ingredients, "not buns." Simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Serve on buns with beans and chips.

title: zesty santa fe salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken paprikash with spaetzle
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden brown.
Add garlic and paprika.
Mix well.
Add cleaned and washed chicken, patted dry, cayenne pepper and salt.
On medium heat saute 10 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Add a few tablespoons of water if chicken sticks to pan.
Add tomato and green pepper.
Cover and simmer slowly until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes.
In small bowl, mix sour cream, flour and 3 tablespoons water with wire whisk until smooth.
Slowly add to chicken while stirring.
Heat through.
Serve with Spaetzle.

title: rose petals potpourri(potpourri adds warmth to a room.)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Tightly pack in a glass jar or Tupperware container, cover and let set for a few days.
Shake to disperse ingredients and potpourri is now ready to use.

title: waldorf turkey toss
directions: In small bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Place in blender and gradually add oil, leaving mixture slightly thick.
Cover and chill.
In large bowl, combine rest of ingredients.
Stir in desired amount of dressing and serve.
Makes 4.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Heat cornstarch in butter.
Thicken.
Add apple cider.
Stir until thickened.
Add raisins when slightly cooled.
Great with ham.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix boiling water and coffee.
Let cool.
Mix sugar with 3 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Cook gently for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Pour the mixtures into a 1/2 gallon jug.
Add 1 fifth inexpensive vodka and 1 whole vanilla bean, split lengthwise.
Store in a dark place for 2 weeks.

title: baked indian pudding
directions: Scald milk and sugar.
Stir in corn meal; cook and stir constantly until smooth and slightly thickened.
Remove from heat. Stir in eggs, cinnamon, ginger, salt, molasses and orange peel. Mix thoroughly.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot topped with ice cream.

title: fruit slush dessert
directions: Thaw orange juice and strawberries.
Cook sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Combine all ingredients and freeze in large container.
Allow enough space in container for stirring later on.
Approximately 1 hour before serving, remove from freezer.
Scoop into dessert cups or parfait glasses; top with fresh strawberries or blueberries.
Serves 20.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pat into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese well with sugar. Add 1 Cool Whip.
Spread over crust; refrigerate.

title: potato salad
directions: Quarter the potatoes; cook and let cool.
Chop eggs and onions very fine.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard to desired taste with all other ingredients.
Add salt and pepper as you like.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in oleo.
In a large bowl, put squash and carrots.
Mix cream, soup and sauteed vegetables. Add squash and carrots. Add the cornbread mix and mix thoroughly. Pour into flat baking dish and bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
When removed from the oven, top with grated cheese.
It will usually melt without putting it back in the oven, but if not, return to oven long enough to melt the cheese. Freeze well, but don't put cheese on before freezing.

title: layered or "forgotten" salad
directions: Start salad with all of the lettuce in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Make a layer of green onions, mushrooms, frozen peas and sliced water chestnuts.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise. Spread mixture completely over salad (this will keep vegetables crisp).
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate up to 3 to 4 days, if needed.
Just before serving, top with noodles and toss.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add lemon, flour, salt and eggs alternately. Pour in ungreased angel food cake pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: knott's beef stew
directions: In a large Dutch oven, heat oil and saute onions and garlic until soft.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Add tomatoes, wine, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, basil, parsley, salt and pepper. Simmer partially covered for 1 hour.

title: marinated artichoke and pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain, rinse and set aside.
Cut tomatoes into quarters or eighths; place in large bowl.
Trim off any tough pieces on artichoke hearts; halve and place in bowl.
Add mushrooms and olives (halve or quarter, if needed); toss gently.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar and oil.
Mix cake according to directions on box.	Bake.
Let cool.
Cut layer in half.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and oil in skillet; then add broccoli and rest of ingredients.
Mix all together and cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat zucchini muffins
directions: Stir the dry ingredients together.
Beat the egg white just until foamy.
Add to the milk, along with the melted butter.
Add the liquid ingredients and the zucchini to the dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.
Spray muffin tin with cooking spray or line with baking cups.
Fill each of the 8 cups 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
You can substitute the zucchini for any fruit such as apples or blueberries or substitute carrots. Calories for one muffin is 124.
Fat is 1.5 grams.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let set 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Serves 10 to 12.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch squares. Brown meat in a tablespoon of hot shortening. Remove meat from skillet; add gravy mix and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Stir in onion, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, ginger and bay leaf with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Add meat. Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove bay leaf. Serve over hot buttered egg noodles.

title: mincemeat oatmeal drops
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg, mincemeat and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening. Add milk and mix.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Spread with half of the sausage.
Roll as for jelly roll. Repeat with remaining dough and sausage.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, slice 1/3 or 1/4 inch thick.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown.
Serve warm.
Freezes well.
Very good when you have a crowd for breakfast.
Make up in advance and freeze.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Mix pudding mix, nutmeg and egg nog; mix well. Add rum extract and whipped cream. Spoon into pie shell and garnish with nutmeg.
Chill 4 hours or until firm.

title: layered salad
directions: Cover with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.

title: pork chops and vegetable bake
directions: For more double recipe.

title: potato bean salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss lightly. Add mayonnaise, stirring to coat vegetables.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken artichoke casserole
directions: Salt, pepper and paprika chicken; brown in 4 tablespoons of the butter.
Arrange chicken in large casserole.
Saute mushrooms in remaining 2 tablespoons of butter for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over the mushrooms and stir in the consomme and sherry; cook for 5 minutes.
Arrange artichokes in between the chicken pieces in the bottom of the casserole.
Pour the sauce over all and cover and bake for 40 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: health salad
directions: Let jello set a while before adding the pineapple and carrots.
Serve with salad dressing.

title: frozen coconut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in freezer.
Take yellow cake out of pan and split. Take first mixture out of freezer and put all but 1 cup between layers of cake.
Mix Cool Whip with remaining cup of the frozen mixture and use for the icing.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Blend butter and cream cheese.
Blend in sugar.
Slowly blend in flour and nuts.
Place teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a spoon or dampened finger.
Bake at 375° only until very lightly browned on edges.
Serve these warm.

title: joanne's jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, clove, nutmeg and salt, then add alternately 1 cup buttermilk and 1 jar blackberry jam.

title: mom's fruit cocktail cookies
directions: In bowl, cream shortening, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs; add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, cloves and baking powder; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in well drained fruit cocktail, nuts and chocolate chips; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoon.
Use large can of fruit cocktail.

title: caramel coconut and pecan pie
directions: Cook coconut and pecans in butter until lightly browned; cool. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and condensed milk.
Put layer in pie crust; put caramel topping.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Put another layer of Cool Whip.
Put caramel icing on top.
Freeze.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Bake cake following recipe on box.
When cake is done, spread condensed milk over cake.
Let milk soak in.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, Crisco and egg white.
Beat at fast speed, then add cream, one teaspoon at a time until well mixed, then add vanilla.
Put in middle of cake and frost.
Put in refrigerator overnight or all day.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown together hamburger and onion.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Serve over tortilla chips. Garnish with grated cheese.

title: chuck wagon meatballs
directions: Beat egg lightly; combine with crumbs, milk and salt.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into balls and brown in hot shortening. While meat browns, cut olives into large pieces.
Put browned meatballs into baking dish.
Heat undiluted soup with vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and olives.
Pour over meatballs and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix together in a bowl eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
When thoroughly mixed, add pineapple, zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Then stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil your chicken in a dutch oven type pot and debone if using a whole chicken and then make pieces bite size. After chicken is ready, add Rotel, cubed velveeta and milk. You may have to add more milk. Melt everything together. Serve over Fritos. This is awesome!

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Line cake pan with rolls. Spread meat on top of rolls. Mix eggs and milk (salt and pepper to taste); pour mixture over meat and dough. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato and pineapple casserole
directions: Melt butter; add pineapple.
Place alternate layers of potatoes and pineapple in a buttered casserole.
Sprinkel with sugar, salt and spices.
Pour liquid over casserole.
Bake in moderate oven, 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add marshmallows. Leave in oven until brown.

title: herb marinade
directions: Wash herbs.
Peel scallions, onions and garlic.
Put in blender with vinegar; add salt.
Store in clean bottles. Refrigerate.

title: really royal rice
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter until clear.
Add mushrooms. Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups of hot water.
Mix all ingredients in electric skillet.
Simmer about 45 minutes on low heat.

title: favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat batter until creamy; gradually beat in peanut butter, then brown sugar, then white sugar.
Beat in eggs, then vanilla. May use 1 1/4 cups flour, 1 cup bran and 3/4 cup oats instead of 3 1/2 cups flour.
In separate bowl, stir together flour and soda. Blend thoroughly into butter mixture.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Crisscross with fork.
Bake at 375° in oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool on baking sheet for about 1 minute.
Transfer to racks and let cool completely.
Store airtight.

title: holiday casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add pizza sauce, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles.
Add vinegar to milk.
Mix cheeses, milk and green pepper together.
Spread 1/2 noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; spread 1/2 meat mixture, then 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whole wheat banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine bananas and buttermilk or yogurt, stirring just enough to mix.
Add dry ingredients alternately with banana mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan to cooling rack.
Especially good re-heated for breakfast.

title: easy quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar, milk and mayonnaise. Stir in flour and mix well.
This dough will be soft.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Saute over slow fire for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in heavy skillet or in oven in shallow, heavy pan.
Good with cocktails dipped in red sauce, or serve as main entree.

title: chicken and noodle soup
directions: Cover chicken with water and add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for several hours. Remove chicken and let cool. Add noodles and cook until tender. Remove chicken from bones and add to pot.

title: melon mold salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar, 1 cup orange juice and mint in double boiler.
Heat to boiling.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, 1 cup orange juice and ice cubes.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Remove any unmelted ice cubes and mint leaves.
Gently fold in fruit.
Turn into 6-cup ring mold; cover and chill until set.
Place on lettuce leaves. Garnish with fruit and mint leaves.
Serve with favorite fruit salad dressing or mayonnaise.

title: sheet cake
directions: Melt margarine and then add the rest of the ingredients. Mix together. Spread part (1/2 of batter) of mixture in a cookie sheet pan. Pour pie filling on top of mixture. Then put rest of mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate at least 24 hours. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: italian potato and tomato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Oil a large casserole with olive oil.
Arrange potatoes, tomatoes and onion in layers, sprinkling each layer with cheese and seasonings.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and seasoning.
Dot with butter and bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: fresh peach crumble
directions: Mix flour, dry milk, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut margarine into flour mixture with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs until smooth. Add flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda and mix well. Fold in apples and nuts. Spread mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or a Bundt pan. Bake at 375° in a preheated oven for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Excellent served with whipped cream on top.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed, using the pineapple juice and the rest water.
Let chill until slightly firm.
Chop up and add pineapple and cottage cheese; fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: carrot salad
directions: Marinate carrots, green pepper and onion in tomato soup.
Mix other ingredients and pour over marinated vegetables.
Let stand for 12 hours.

title: deli platter
directions: Clean and section vegetables.
Arrange them on a tray lined with greens and serve with dips.

title: cocktail snack
directions: Mix equal parts of apple jelly and pineapple preserves.
Add horseradish to taste.
Serve over cream cheese.
Use as a spread over crackers.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain first 3 ingredients, reserving juice; set aside. Combine next 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan; stir well.
Add reserved fruit juice and bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat.

title: cheese logs
directions: Mix all but paprika together with hands. Roll into logs and roll in paprika. Can wrap individual logs in foil and freeze.

title: cabbage-wedge casserole
directions: Cut in wedges of cabbage along with butter.
Arrange onion, beef and rice between wedges.
Bring water, salt and pepper to boil and then mix tomatoes together.
Pour liquid over it.
Cover in foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy chicken and rice soup
directions: Combine rice and water in a large saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add chicken broth to rice in saucepan.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Saute green pepper, celery, onion, carrot, mushrooms and garlic in margarine in a large skillet until tender.
Stir in flour and cook over medium heat 1 to 2 minutes. Add chicken, parsley, pimiento, salt, pepper and rice mixture to mixture in skillet.
Stir in evaporated skim milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture is thoroughly heated (do not boil).
Yield:
2 quarts.
Serving size:
1 cup. (Low cholesterol recipe.)

title: maidrites
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: wind cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add cream of tartar.
Beat to mix.
In second bowl, beat egg yolks and water a long time until like heavy cream.
Beat in sugar; add salt and vanilla.
Gradually add flour to egg mixture.
Fold in egg whites.

title: tamale chili pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer chips on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 small casserole dishes.
Lay tamales on top of chips. Pour chili over all.
Top with chopped onion and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Top with sour cream, salsa and jalapeno peppers, if desired.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes at 400°. Brush top with melted margarine when done.

title: chicken and swiss vegetable medley
directions: Cook chicken (breasts or thighs) ahead and debone.
Place in dish that has been sprayed with Pam or butter.
Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can of fried onions.
Pour into dish with chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Coat meat with flour mixed with pepper.
Brown meat in a large skillet in the oleo.
Add the mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Brown meat, then add bouillon cubes and water.
Stir until cubes are dissolved, then cover and cook 45 minutes (stirring occasionally) on low heat or until tender.
Then stir in one cup of sour cream and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked egg noodles or rice.

title: chicken and cashews
directions: Marinate chicken in
soy
sauce,
sherry and cornstarch for 2 to 4 hours.
Heat oil in a medium-high wok.
Add chicken and onions and	cook
quickly,	stirring
constantly.
Add cashews; heat slightly and serve with rice.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Roll sausage into balls.
Fry the sausage and drain.
Layer potatoes and sausage; add onion.
Mix milk and soup together. Pour over sausage and potatoes.
Cover and bake at 325° until potatoes are done, for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: microwave popcorn
directions: Microwave
directions:	Pour popcorn into a small paper bag. Twist
top	lightly to let steam escape, leaving lots of room for the
corn
to
pop.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes.
Pour into
a
large
bowl.
Spray popcorn with Pam and salt and serve.

title: sauteed cocktail tomatoes
directions: Heat butter or oil in skillet.
Add garlic and heat; do not brown.
Add vegetables and sugar.
Stir with wooden spoon over high heat for 3 minutes. Serves 4.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a glass baking dish, melt the butter.
Mix together the sugar, flour and milk.
Line pan with any type of fruit.
Pour batter over fruit. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Mix butter, 1 cup sugar and flour, a little at a time.
Pat in jelly roll pan.
Roll with rolling pin until smooth.
Then fork all over.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cut into bars right away, while hot.
Sprinkle with sugar or powdered sugar.
Set on rack to cool.

title: easy corn fondue
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Beat egg yolks until light and fluffy.
Add corn, bacon fat, onion, cheese, salt and milk. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into corn mixture.
Pour in greased pan, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch.
Top with crushed chips. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until firm.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine pudding and sugar.
Stir in milk, vanilla and syrup. Add cherries and bits of chocolate bar.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Pour pineapple into bottom of pan.
Cover with cake mix right from the box.
Top that with coconut, then chopped nuts.
Drizzle melted butter or margarine over top of everything.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Split chicken breasts and pound to 1/4-inch thickness.
Dredge in flour and brown in olive oil over medium heat (6 to 7 minutes). Transfer to a large baking dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute squash, onion and 1/2 stick butter until squash is tender.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine dry Stove Top, seasoning packet and 1 1/2 sticks butter (melted).
Press 1/2 into bottom of casserole dish.
Combine squash mixture with onion dip, mushroom soup and pepper.
Pour over stuffing in casserole dish, then crumble the remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix well and put in a greased pan about the size of a number 8 skillet.
Over this, put drained cherries from can.
To juice, add enough water to make 2 cups.
To this, add 1 3/4 cups sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and dash of nutmeg.
Let raise to a boil and pour over batter and cherries.
Bake about 45 minutes.
Do not try to remove from pan until ready to serve.
Make this of berries and peaches, too.
Before baking it looks like a hopeless mess, but try it.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and flour; add pecans and mix well. Shape 1 tablespoon per cookie into balls; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Combine confectioners and granulated sugars.
Roll balls in sugars while still hots. Makes 4 dozen.

title: saucy apple swirl
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together. Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Dust with 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: turkey-eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Spray large nonstick saucepan with cooking spray and heat. Add turkey, onion and garlic. Cook, stirring as needed until turkey is browned and onion is softened, 5 to 6 minutes. Add eggplant, tomatoes, peppers, bread crumbs and basil. Bring to a boil, stirring as needed. Transfer turkey mixture to baking dish. Bake, covered, until vegetables are tender, 45 to 50 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and bake until cheese is lightly browned, about 15 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Yield: 8 servings.

title: ilah's chicken and rice
directions: In casserole place rice, chicken and soups.
Cover with butter, cheese and almonds.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: mexican pizza(appetizer)
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over evenly and layer remaining ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hill country pecan spread
directions: Using an electric mixer, blend together softened cream cheese and milk. Stir in dried beef, green pepper, onion, sour cream, garlic, pepper and jalapenos.
Mix well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together dry ingredients (flour, soda and salt).
In very large mixing bowl, beat sugars, oleo and vanilla until creamy. Add eggs.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: fish and chips
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Cut into pieces, 1 x 3-inch (or so). Cut potatoes into similar pieces (1 x 3-inch).
Combine flour and salt.
Add egg yolk, water and oil.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in egg white.
Fry potatoes in deep fat at 375° until golden brown. Drain and keep warm.
Dip fish in 1/4 cup flour and then in batter.
Fry until golden brown, at least 1 1/2 minutes per side.

title: grandma's peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a bowl mix together melted butter, softened butter, and sugar until grainy. In the pie crust add half the sugar mixture; arrange peaches in the pie shell. Sprinkle the rest of the sugar on top. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: potica
directions: Measure flour.
Sift flour.
Sift with 3 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Cut in butter (as in pie crust).
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let stand until foams. Mix egg yolks and cream.
Add foaming yeast.
Make dent in flour; add mixture.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Place 1/2 of chili in bottom of greased casserole.
Cover with half of corn chips, onion, and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: texas lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown meat and drain. Add salt and seasonings, tomatoes, sauce and chilies. Mix well.
Simmer uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: wimpies
directions: Fry hamburg slowly; drain.
Put all ingredients in a pot.
Put in with slotted spoon.
Cook slowly 45 minutes to an hour.

title: priest's ragout
directions: Brown cubes in butter.
Add garlic and pearl onions; brown again with meat for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add peppers (red and black); paprika can be substituted if you don't want it spicy.
Add allspice, cinnamon, salt and 4 cups of water.
(All spices are by taste, vary amounts as needed.)
Cook for 3 hours over medium-low heat until meat is very tender.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Use only real butter.
Put all ingredients in large bowl. Using your hands, knead all together until it becomes one mass. This will take time, be patient.
Form into 6 balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
With heel of hand and fingers, press into round cakes 1/2-inch thick.
Flute edges with fork; mark into pie shaped sections with back of knife and decorate with fork pricks. Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not let brown.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from rack with pancake turner.
When cool, break along marks to serve.
Can be frozen.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: casual cream cheese cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place butter, sugar, cream cheese, egg and vanilla in a bowl and beat with electric mixer until blended. Add flour and beat until well blended.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets, spacing cookies 1 inch apart.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: scallops with fresh tomato
directions: If using scallops, cut each crosswise in half; set aside.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, cook margarine, lemon juice, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons water on High 1 to 2 minutes until margarine is melted.
Arrange scallops or fish fillets in margarine mixture and stir to coat scallops.
(Turn fillets to coat both sides.)
Cook, covered, on High 2 to 3 minutes until scallops or fillets are opaque.
Stir in tomato; cook 1 to 2 minutes until tomato is warm. Sprinkle fish with green onion, dill and paprika.
Spoon sauce over fish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour in 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cake will fall in center.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend all ingredients with electric mixer or food blender. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn with finely chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste, then pour in small baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over the top and add chunks of butter.
Pour in milk until it comes to the top of the dish.
Bake in uncovered dish at 400° until browned.
Also delicious with green beans instead of corn.

title: cranberry meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all except 1/2 can of cranberry sauce.
Shape and form into loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Before the last 15 minutes, pour remaining cranberry sauce over loaf and bake for the final 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: All juice must be drained from crushed pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in crushed pecans.
Ready to serve with crackers of choice.

title: krieger vegetable soup
directions: Simmer the meat, soup bones, water, salt, peppercorns, quartered onions, parsley stalks of celery, 2 cups diced tomatoes and quartered carrots in a covered pan for 4 to 5 hours.
Remove bones and meat.
Discard bones and cut meat in small pieces; set aside to add to stock later.
Strain stock and combine with diced potatoes, sliced carrots, diced celery, snap beans and 1 1/2 quarts diced tomatoes.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender, but crisp.
Add meat and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini and cut off ends.
Steam until nearly done.
Cut in half lengths.
Remove center pulp and combine with other ingredients.
Fill shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party slush punch
directions: Mix jello, hot water and sugar together until jello is dissolved.
Add all other ingredients except ginger ale.
Put in containers and freeze.
I use butter tubs or freezer bags.
Take out of freezer 3 hours before serving.
Place in punch bowl and pour ginger ale over.
Mix together.
This will be slushy.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine in large bowl.

title: bavarian goulash
directions: Trim beef, if necessary.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Heat the oil or butter in a heavy saucepan.
Add the beef and saute until evenly browned on all sides.
Add the onions and saute until nearly translucent.
Add the tomatoes and season to taste with salt, pepper and paprika.
Add the bay leaf and pour into the stock; stir well.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until the beef is tender.
In a small bowl, combine the flour and a small amount of the wine.
Stir this into the goulash.
Cook over a low heat until the sauce is thickened.
Serve with potato dumplings or white bread dumplings, boiled or mashed potatoes.
Pasta or rice may also be served.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Peel, seed and chop tomatoes.
Allow to drain in colander. Chop onions and peppers.
In a large pot on high heat, combine all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce to medium heat.
Cook; stir occasionally.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until very thick.
Near the end, stir often to prevent sticking.
Spoon into hot sterile jars; allow 1/4-inch headroom.
Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes or in pressure cooker for 10 minutes at 5 pounds.
Double batch makes 8 to 9 pints.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In medium-size saucepan over medium heat, combine rice, 1 1/2 cups milk, sugar and Sweet One.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes or until thick and slightly creamy.
Beat remaining 1/2 cup milk and egg; stir into rice mixture.
Stir in raisins. Without letting mixture boil, continue cooking 2 minutes.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
(Mixture will thicken on standing.) Transfer to serving bowl; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve warm or cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.
Calories:
120 per 1/2 cup.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cream together with mixer. Pour in 9 x 13 pan.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve on lettuce and garnish with maraschino cherries.
Serves 12.

title: tennessee state cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugars.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Ground your hamburger.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; boil noodles, then start layering hamburger, noodles, Ricotta cheese, sliced cheese and Mozzarella cheese until at the top of a 9 x 12-inch sheet pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: skillet meal for two
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over low heat.
Combine ham, broccoli, potatoes and onions in skillet.
Cook and stir until potatoes are brown.
Reduce heat, add grated cheese and continue heating until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat and divide into two plates.
Top each with 1 tablespoon sour cream.

title: stuffed chicken shells
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Remove skin and bones and finely chop.
Add salt, pepper, onion and celery and mix together. Add just enough mayonnaise to hold mixture together.
Cook jumbo shells as directed on box.
Drain shells and stuff with chicken mixture.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and chilies.
Put 1/2 of this mixture mixed with meat in tortillas, about 2 to 4 tablespoons per tortilla.
It works best to heat each tortilla on a dry pan about 10 seconds before putting mixture in.
Roll up and place side by side in cake pan or jelly roll pan.
Pour rest of sauce over top and sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and center is heated.
Do not overbake. May be prepared the day before and refrigerated.
Baking time slightly longer.

title: chocolate crunches
directions: Melt chocolate bits in top of double boiler over water.
Add peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Toss gently until mixture is thoroughly and evenly coated.
Drop from teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Chill to harden.
Makes 24 clusters.

title: chicken and split-pea soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, vegetables and seasonings in a 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven.
Stir in peas.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until peas are very tender and vegetables are tender.
Stir in chicken and ham.
Cool. Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.

title: dip delight
directions: Spread the cream cheese in a pie plate.
Cover with salsa. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: ruth's sugar cookies
directions: Sift into a large bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Make a well and add shortening. Mix until smooth. Cover tightly and store overnight.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 8 minutes at 425°.

title: edible flowers for salads
directions: To crystalize petals:
dip in egg white, then superfine sugar; let dry.

title: lynn's chicken
directions: Thoroughly blend ingredients together; lay chicken on top. Cover with tinfoil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: glazed hot dogs
directions: Cut wieners in bite-size pieces.
Place mustard and jelly into a skillet.
Cook over low heat until melted.
Add wieners and simmer until they are puffy.

title: old fashioned chicken pie
directions: Boil the chicken.
Save the broth.
In a large deep pie pan, put cooked chicken and broth.
Make stiff dough for crust and dumplings.
Bring chicken and broth to boil.
Add dumplings. Reduce heat to low.
Let cook 10 minutes.
Break eggs into the hot mixture.
Add sweet milk; season to taste with pepper and salt. Make the crust.
Put the crust on top and bake in 400° oven until brown.
Spread the butter on top of the crust when done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Use a number 8 or number 10 iron skillet; heat in oven.
Cover bottom of skillet with half the cornbread mixture.
Sprinkle the grated cheese on top and cover with remainder of cornbread mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: alpine chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini carrot casserole
directions: Boil the zucchini, onions and water together for 5 minutes and drain.
Stir in the soup, sour cream and carrots.
Toss the stuffing mix with the melted butter.
Spread half of the stuffing in bottom of a 12 x 7-inch or 2 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mix on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over all. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: heavenly rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and pineapple and boil for 20 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the strawberry jello until dissolved. Pour into jars and seal with a double coating of new paraffin. Makes 9 (8 ounce) jars.

title: scrambled wieners
directions: Saute cut up wieners in butter with the chopped onion.
Add 2 eggs, scrambled, for each wiener used.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: bean sandwiches
directions: Place bread slices on a baking sheet and toast 1 side.
Turn bread over and spoon beans on bread to generously cover.
Sprinkle onions on top; then add 1 slice cheese and top with thin sliced bacon.
Broil until bacon is done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Turn into a 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle the top with crushed cereal flakes.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tomato salad
directions: Heat mixture of vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed, salt, sugar and water to boiling for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over vegetables and mix well.
Let stand.
Serve.
Will last for several days.

title: warm chicken spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese and 1 cup Cheddar cheese, sour cream, onion, sherry, bouillon and garlic powder until smooth.
Stir in chicken and almonds.
Spread in 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pat into pie shells.
Bake at 325° to 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: green tomato relish
directions: In a grinder or food processor, coarsely grind tomatoes, red bell peppers, green bell peppers, and onions.
(You may need to do this in batches.)
Line a large colander with cheesecloth, place in sink or in a large bowl, and pour in tomato mixture to drain for 1 hour.
In a large, non-aluminum stockpot, combine tomato mixture, celery seed, mustard seed, salt, sugar, and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and simmer over low heat 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Sterilize enough jars and lids to hold relish (12 one-pint jars, or 6 one-quart jars).
Pack relish into sterilized jars, making sure there are no spaces or air pockets.
Fill jars all the way to top. Screw on lids.
Place a rack in the bottom of a large stockpot and fill halfway with boiling water.
Carefully lower jars into pot using a holder.
Leave a 2 inch space between jars.
Pour in more boiling water if necessary, until tops of jars are covered 2 inches of water.
Bring water to a full boil, then cover and process for 30 minutes.
Remove jars from pots and place on cloth-covered surface, several inches apart, until cool.
Once cool, press top of each lid with finger, ensuring that seal is tight.
Relish can be stored for up to a year.
Makes 192 servings.

title: gail's favorite
directions: Relax in bathtub; put on make-up.
Comb and brush hair.
Put on clothes.
Then have husband take me out for potato skins at Damons.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Sprinkle chocolate chips over milk.
Sprinkle coconut over chips. Sprinkle nuts over coconut.
Bake for 25 minutes or until lightly browned in preheated oven at 350°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Spray a large baking dish with Pam.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix sugar and cream cheese, then add 6 ounces of Cool Whip.
Then spread into crust layer.
Mix vanilla and chocolate pudding with milk; beat until thick.
Spread over other layer, then spread 6 ounces Cool Whip over pudding layer and top with chopped nuts, M&M's or other decorations.

title: antipasta salad
directions: On a large platter or individual plates, arrange some or all of the ingredients listed.
Make it attractive.
Serve with Italian dressing or dressing of your choice.
Serve with warm crusty bread.
Makes a nice cool meal.

title: cumin rice casserole
directions: Heat rice, onion and pepper in bacon fat until golden brown. Combine in 2-quart casserole with remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: twice cooked divinity
directions: Stir sugar into corn syrup, water and salt, until dissolved. Boil to medium-ball stage (240°).
Beat egg whites until stiff. Pour 1/3 of syrup over egg whites.
Beating constantly, cook remaining syrup to very hard ball stage (265°).
Beat syrup into candy mixture.
Continue beating until stiff.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When mixture holds its shape when dropped from a spoon, add vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen pieces.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into oiled iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: dutch doughnuts
directions: Heat Crisco or oil (2 to 3-inches) to 375°.

Beat milk, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup oil, eggs, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and 1 cup flour in a large mixing bowl on low speed, scraping sides constantly for 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed, scraping sides of bowl occasionally for 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour and currants.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into vegetable shortening.
Turn doughnuts as they rise to the surface. Fry until brown, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll doughnuts in powdered sugar.
For non-sugar users, sprinkle lightly with a sugar substitute.
Makes about 30 doughnuts.

title: split pea soup
directions: Combine water, split peas, ham, onion and seasonings in 5-quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 40 minutes, stirring several times during cooking.
Remove bone; cut off meat and dice.
Return meat to soup.
Add vegetables.
Microwave, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes or until soup is desired thickness and vegetables are tender, stirring several times during cooking. Makes 2 quarts.

title: plain pickles
directions: Put jars in cold water.
Fill
pot
to	neck
of
jars. Bring to a boil.	Take out and turn upside-down for 7 hours or overnight.

title: chicken saronno
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch wide strips.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder and curry powder.
Roll strips into flour. Heat butter in a large skillet.
Brown chicken.
Add mushrooms and Amaretto.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix chicken broth and cornstarch. Stir mixture into skillet.
Stir over low heat until mixture bubbles and thickens.
Season to taste with salt, if necessary. Serve over patty shell, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: favorite pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and seasonings in skillet until beef is brown.
Add soup, water and noodles.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap dry chestnuts in bacon and secure with toothpick.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Drain grease.
Pour over a mixture of brown sugar and catsup.
Bake for an additional 1/2 hour.

title: hamburg cookies
directions: Color frosting to make catsup (red) and mustard (yellow). Color coconut green for lettuce.
Make hamburgers by layering wafer, red frosting, mint wafer, yellow
frosting, green coconut and wafer.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cocktail rye appetizer
directions: Spread Philadelphia cream cheese on rye bread.
Slice tomatoes and place on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Pie is done when knife blade inserted near center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.

title: oatmeal and coconut cookies
directions: Mix margarine, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by walnut size balls on cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar or flour.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: country fried cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour boiling water over dry ingredients until mixed well.
Wet hands and pat out hand size patties.
Fry in iron skillet in very hot oil.
Brown on one side and turn.
It is very important to keep oil very hot.
This is delicious with any kind of greens, beans or peas.

title: d j's chicken delight
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry; add chicken to a skillet.
Combine the soup mix with 1 cup of water and pour over chicken.
Add chopped mushrooms.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour over medium heat.
Serve with rice.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in saucepan.
Bring slowly to boil, stirring constantly and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat until lukewarm (set pan in cold water while beating to shorten the cooling time).
Add vanilla. Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: popsicles
directions: Into a 50-ounce canister, put all ingredients, except cold water.
Shake to mix.
Add the cold water.
Pour into ice tubs and freeze.
Makes 20.
Nice texture.
Don't drip while you are eating them.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine eggs, milk and pineapple together.
Add broken bread; put sugar with mixture and add melted butter.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
The mixture can be placed in the refrigerator overnight before baking, if desired.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat until smooth. Add cornmeal to cream.
Add to first mixture.
Add flavoring. Stir until smooth. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° to 375° until pie is set and crust is brown.

title: orchard punch
directions: In a punch bowl or large pitcher,
combine juices,
lemon and lime.
Chill.
Just before serving add club soda.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form into balls about the size of walnuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 400°. Freezes well.
Warm to serve.
Makes about 5 dozen balls.

title: mom's applesauce cake loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan. Beat brown sugar and margarine in a large bowl with electric mixer on high speed for 2 minutes.
Beat in egg, vanilla and applesauce. Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan; remove from pan to wire rack.
Cool completely before slicing.
Yield:
1 loaf (24 slices).

title: fudge's fudge
directions: Grease 13x9 in. pan.
Mix margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 qt. pan.
Bring to a full rolling boil on medium heat; stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes on medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234 degrees.
