Remove from heat. Stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pan.
Cool at room temperature.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 70 minutes.

title: herbed asparagus
directions: Steam asparagus until tender.
Keep warm.
In a small skillet, melt butter and saute garlic over medium heat.
Remove garlic. Stir in chives, parsley, lemon juice and salt, heat thoroughly. Place asparagus in serving dish and pour sauce over.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet-sour shrimp
directions: In saucepan, blend cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in chicken broth.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and butter.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to boiling.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes longer.
Add pea pods and shrimp; heat through.
Serve on hot rice.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: chinese fried rice with shrimp
directions: Mix rice, mushroom soy and m.s.g. (rice should be brown in color).
Prepare shrimp with salt and pepper and Chinese 5 spice. Heat 6 tablespoons cooking oil and 2 tablespoons sesame oil in large wok.
Stir-fry carrots and onion about 4 minutes.
Take out, leaving oil only in wok.
Put in eggs with salt and pepper; stir and put aside.
(Eggs can be cooked in a separate pan as the residue from the fried eggs may burn.)
Stir-fry shrimp for 5 minutes.
Add rice; stir.
Add cooked carrots, onion, eggs and scallions.
Stir-fry until they are all mixed properly and rice is hot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla. Mix until smooth. Fold in whipped topping, half at a time. Spoon into pie shell. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion
in a 1 3/4-quart dish on High for 5 to 7 minutes or
until
meat
is
brown and onion is tender, stirring once.
Transfer
meat
to medium mixing bowl; stir in tomato sauce, water
and
chili powder.
Set aside.
Drain and wipe out casserole.
Mash
half of the kidney beans (3/4 cup). Add to casserole.
Stir
in
taco
sauce
and remaining beans. Spread evenly
in
bottom
casserole.
Spread
meat mixture on top. Cover and
microwave
on
High
to 8 minutes or until heated through.
To serve, sprinkle with cheese, then lettuce, tomato, olives and tortilla chips.

title: garlic dill pickles(servings:  6 quarts)
directions: Pack 6 sterilized quart jars with onion, garlic, dill, alum and cucumbers in that order.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to boil. Fill each jar, leaving some headspace.
Process in hot water bath.

title: church window candy
directions: In a large saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over very low heat.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in marshmallows and 1/4 cup nuts.
Divide mixture in half and shape each half into a log, 1 1/2 inches in diameter and 6 inches long.
Roll each in remaining nuts; chill.
Slice logs into 1/2-inch slices.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook the 2 cups of macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Add other ingredients.
Put into greased dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in a saucepan.
Mix with chicken and dressing.
Put in greased dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until set.

title: simple dessert
directions: Let jell until firm.
Whip cream and add to jello.
Whip all together.
Top with a cherry.

title: cream chillies corn
directions: Mix together by hand the cream cheese and butter.
Fold corn and peppers into cream mixture.
Bake 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Chill Pet milk for several hours.
Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add lemon juice and cool.
Cream the cream cheese. Add sugar, then vanilla and cooled jello mixture.

title: lois' prune cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and spices.
Combine prunes and nuts.
Beat sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla until light.
Add soda to buttermilk and add alternately with flour mixture to the creamed mixture. Fold in the prunes and nuts.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pour Hot Prune Cake Glaze slowly on hot cake.

title: shrimp louisiana
directions: Heat butter; add onions.
Cook until brown.
Add shrimp; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add pepper, salt, onion tops and parsley; cook 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 10 servings.

title: spicy rib stew
directions: In skillet brown sausage, onion, salt and garlic; stir in tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes, chilies, bouillon and oregano. Set aside.
Cut ribs into 2 rib portions and brown in skillet.
Add ribs to stew; spooning juices over.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Meanwhile, cut zucchini into 1/2 inch slices and red or green pepper into chunks.
Add to stew, spooning juice over. Bake, covered, for 20 minutes more or until ribs are no longer pink.

title: uncooked candy
directions: Melt butter.
Combine all ingredients and add to butter.
Form into small balls by hand (size is a personal choice).
Set onto wax paper or cookie sheet to harden.

title: tree cookies
directions: Mix baking powder, flour and sugar.
Cut butter in as for pastry, until very finely divided.
Add slightly beaten eggs, reserving one egg white to brush tops of cookies, and vanilla. Work mix lightly but persistently until smooth dough is made. Chill 1 or 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Take a small amount. Roll out on board.
Cut into any desired shape.
Bake on sheets at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Decorate.

title: pecan yeast rolls
directions: Put rolls in Bundt pan, well-greased or sprayed with "Pam". Sprinkle rolls with pecans.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle pudding mix over top of rolls.
Pour melted butter over all.
Set on counter overnight; cover lightly with tea towel.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes and invert on plate.

title: marinade for beef
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir well.
Add meat.
Cover and marinate 12 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
To cook, remove meat from marinade, reserving marinade.
Baste with marinade while cooking.

title: cherry punch
directions: Mix the ingredients well together.

title: pineapple cranberry relish
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple.
Chop orange and cranberries into coarse pieces in food processor or blender.
Pour into bowl.
Add pineapple and sugar.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 cups.

title: hot water pastry
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over shortening and salt and beat until smooth and creamy.
Stir in sifted flour until a smooth ball
is formed.
Cover
with waxed paper or plastic wrap and chill
until firm.
Makes
enough
for a 2-crust pie or 2 pie shells.
This pastry is easy to handle.
It can be frozen and it will keep for a week in the refrigerator.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix cucumbers with salt and onion.
Refrigerate for two hours. Then drain off juice, getting out as much as possible, but don't rinse.

title: cranberry fruit and nut bread
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix. Stir in vanilla.
Fold in cranberries, pecans, raisins and apricots.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle the powdered sugar and milk mixture over loaves.

title: mom fritsch's french dressing
directions: Mix vinegar, catsup, oil and sugar.
Add onion and pepper; shake well.
Refrigerate overnight; then remove onion.
Shake before using.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Make pudding according to package directions.
Mix in softened cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Roll out Oreos as fine as possible.
(Advisable to use a blender or food processor.) Alternate layers of pudding mixture and cookies, ending with cookies which looks like dirt on top.
I have a plastic flowerpot I use for this only and I have some silk flowers I put on top. Remove flowers before eating.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
(Mixture will be thick.)

title: angel eggs
directions: Hard-boil the eggs.
Slice eggs in two lengthwise.
Scrape out the cooked egg yolk and put in small bowl; add the mayo, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Blend together.
Fill empty egg halves with mixture.
If desired, sprinkle with paprika.

title: pumpkin bread(serves 12)
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour a 3 x 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and line bottom with brown paper and grease and flour paper.
Bake at 355° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Scald 1 3/4 cups milk with chocolate in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Measure cornstarch in small mixing bowl and blend with remaining 1/4 cup milk.
Mix in sugar and salt.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Add quickly all at once to scalded chocolate milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Cool. Pour in baked shell.
Top with whip cream or make your own meringue.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage well.
Beat eggs and all ingredients.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham, cabbage and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion, garlic and red pepper.
Cook until soft.
Sprinkle with sugar; cook 5 minutes, then sprinkle with vinegar.
Add cabbage, salt and pepper.
Reduce to medium heat and cook, covered, for 20 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.
Cook noodles; drain and add to cabbage mixture, along with ham.
Stir over heat until noodles are golden and ham is heated through.
Mm, mm good!!

title: glazed pecans
directions: Put nuts in bowl with grated orange rind and stir.
Let stand. Cook
water
and
sugar until it spins a thread.
Pour over until they
turn white or well coated.
Put nuts on waxed paper to cool.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Preheat oven at 325°. Pour 1/4 cup salsa mix in baking dish and place chicken breasts on top.

Pour rest of salsa over chicken. Cover and bake 40 minutes. Remove from oven and place slice of cheese on top of each chicken breast. Re-cover baking dish and let sit 10 minutes to allow cheese to melt.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients until fluffy.
Spread cream cheese mixture in plate.
Spread crabmeat and chili over cream cheese. Serve with crackers.

title: diabetic whipped topping
directions: Chill small bowl and beaters.
Combine milk and water in bowl. Beat until stiff.
Add Equal and vanilla.
Serve immediately. Makes 2 servings.

title: tortilla delights
directions: Mix ingredients; spread on tortillas, roll and cut to 1-inch lengths.
Serve chilled.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour half of mixture into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix together apples, cranberries and white sugar.
Spread in bottom of a casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, oatmeal and flour to make a crumbly mixture.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: concord jello
directions: Mix jello (dry) and cream cheese together.
Add hot water, then cold water.
Cool quickly.
Place blueberries on top and whipped cream.
(Peaches, if desired, may be used.)

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and add syrup.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk.
Start in cold oven at 300° and bake for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: tuscan bean soup
directions: In a large pot, saute garlic and onions in olive oil, then add soaked and drained white beans. Add carrots.

Squeeze and add plum tomatoes plus juice. Add fresh basil and a few pinches of red pepper. Cover with water or stock, salt and pepper to taste and cook for 1 hour. Adjust seasonings and cook until tender. Clean and cut escarole. Saute escarole in oil until it shrinks and add to soup.

title: pickled jalapeno peppers
directions: Pierce peppers in several places.
Pack into 2-quart canning jar or several smaller ones of choice.
Heat remaining ingredients over medium heat to boiling point.
Pour over peppers; tighten lids.
Let stand 2 weeks at room temperature before using. Refrigerate after opening.

title: chicken
directions: Remove giblets.
Wash roast.
Season to taste inside and out. Place 2 strips uncooked bacon and 1 medium onion inside roast.
Tie legs and fold wings.
Cook regularly.
Remove from oven and place on platter.
Bring cream and broth to boil in saucepan.
Reduce heat and add Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
Stir constantly until cheese melts and becomes smooth.
Spoon over carved roaster and sprinkle with 6 strips, crisp, cooked and crumbled bacon.

title: rotel dip with meat
directions: Mix ground beef with taco seasoning according to directions on taco seasoning pack.
Add cheese and tomatoes.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: apple dopple
directions: Cream sugar oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box; then drain.
Mix milk and cornstarch together in saucepan.
Add butter and cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Slowly add cheese until melted.
Put macaroni into 2-quart casserole. Add sauce; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until brown and bubbly.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Remove bacon from large frying pan, crumble and set aside to add to lettuce just before serving.
To fryings in pan, add vinegar, water and sugar or sugar substitute.
Bring to boil.
Add large bowl of lettuce; keep stirring and turning lettuce in pan until thoroughly coated with vinegar sauce and wilted.
Lift lettuce from liquid, add crumbled bacon tossed in lightly and serve warm.
The liquid may be saved for another preparation, just add a bit of fresh vinegar.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: no mess easy pie crust
directions: Measure flour into bowl and add salt.
Combine oil and water. Add to flour and salt.
Stir with fork.
Roll between 2 pieces waxed paper.

title: alphabet minestrone
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium-high heat, warm the oil until hot, but not smoking.
Add garlic and saute for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add broth, tomatoes, zucchini, carrots, celery, green beans, potatoes, chickpeas, pasta, fennel seed, basil and oregano. Bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer until pasta and vegetables are cooked through, 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and serve hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together oil and sugar.
Sift together next 6 ingredients. Mix dry ingredients with pumpkin, adding eggs one at a time and beating well after each.
Add vanilla, pecans, raisins and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into large tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting or eat plain.

title: mexican rice
directions: Saut onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until onions are opaque. Add rice and saut until rice is lightly browned. Add the tomato sauce, beef broth and Tabasco. Simmer, covered, until liquid is absorbed (approximately 20 minutes). This is a great side dish with steak.

title: rum punch
directions: Mix sugar and 2 cups pineapple juice.
Heat over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Put in small containers and freeze.

title: white bean chili
directions: Sort and rinse beans. Place in a large Dutch oven. Cover with water 2-inches above beans. Let soak overnight. Drain; set beans aside.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Boil butter, water and cocoa together.
Add flour and sugar; beat well.
Add sour cream, vanilla and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in oblong pan.

title: tantalizing baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients in blender.
Coat chicken pieces with oat mixture.
Dip into milk, then again into the oat mixture.
Place in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until juices run clear when pierced with fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Add flour and milk.
Alternate adding flavoring and nuts.
Bake 2 hours at 250° or 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: First, peel and cut apples in square chunks, about the size of a thimble.
Sprinkle in cinnamon and 5 tablespoons of sugar; set aside.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together and roll into balls.
Press with fork; put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° until light brown.

title: coconut honey bars
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, honey and vanilla until smooth, stir in oats and coconut; mix well.
Spread in well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or just until golden.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars. Makes 24 bars.

title: "too good to share" brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, pecans and 1 egg together.
Press in 9 x
13-inch	pan.
Mix
cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar. Pour
over	first layer.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: baked bananas(guatemala)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 F. Peel bananas and cut in half lengthwise. Place in greased baking dish and dot them with the margarine. Mix the honey and lemon juice and pour over the bananas. Bake for 15 minutes. Serve hot with sour cream or yogurt, sprinkle with nuts and raisins. Serves 4.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute onions and pepper in oil.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Add to sauteed onions and pepper.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Great with chicken or brisket.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix and pour into buttered pie plate.
Cook at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour in buttered baking dish.

title: mayor bill roberts' microwave caramel corn
directions: Mix together brown sugar, margarine, Karo syrup and salt. Microwave on High 3 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Remove and stir in soda.
Pour over corn in paper bag, stirring or shake it well.
Put bag in microwave for 1 minute and heat 15 seconds on High.
Take out and shake the bag.
Put back in microwave for 1 minute and 15 seconds on High.
Take the bag out and shake.
Put back in microwave for 30 seconds.
Take out and spread on cookie sheets to cool.

title: diane's tuna cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into ball and refrigerate.
Before serving, roll in chopped walnuts.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; set aside 2 tablespoons salmon juice.
Mix salmon, egg and onion.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to juice.
Stir in mixture.
Fry in Crisco.

title: champagne chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; lightly dredge chicken in flour mixture.
Heat butter and olive oil in large skillet.
Add chicken; saute on each side about 4 minutes each.
Add champagne (or wine); cook over medium heat about 12 minutes, or until chicken is done. Remove chicken; set aside.
Add mushrooms and whipping cream to skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until just thickened.
Add chicken; cook until heated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese, chips and almonds.
Refrigerate overnight and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 12.

title: low calorie spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Serve with non-fat crackers or use with carrot sticks, celery or green or red bell peppers.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, milk and eggs in bowl, beating until smooth. Pour 1/4 cup into funnel and release into skillet with hot oil. Move funnel in circular motion to form spiral. Fry until edges are golden brown. Turn and fry on other side. Drain on paper towel. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or syrup.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake potatoes until fork-tender.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Slowly blend in flour with whisk until thoroughly blended.
Gradually add milk to the butter flour mixture, whisking constantly.
Whisk in salt and pepper and simmer over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cut potato peels and discard the remainder (i.e. use more peel).
When milk mixture is very hot, whisk in potatoes, green onion and potato peel.
Whisk well and add sour cream and crumbled bacon.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cheese, a little at a time, until all is melted.
Garnish with chives, green onions, cheese and bacon.
Serves 8.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine and place in baking dish.
In a shallow dish or plastic bag, combine remaining ingredients except chicken.
Coat chicken with flour mixture, then dip in melted margarine to lightly coat.
Place chicken on a baking rack and place rack in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes; turn and bake 15 minutes more or until done.

title: bean soup
directions: Place beans in a Dutch oven or soup kettle; add water to cover by 2 inches.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from the heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain.
Add broth, water, ham bone, seasonings and bouillon.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Saute onions, carrots and celery in oil; add to soup.
Cover and simmer 1 hour longer. Debone ham and cut into chunks; return to soup.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add stewed tomatoes, tomato soup, macaroni and water.
Bring to boil, then simmer until macaroni is tender.
Add corn and simmer for 10 more minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and add 1 can whole kernel corn with juice and 1 can cream-style corn.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate mint bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and cocoa; cook until smooth.
Add egg; cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and crumbs.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: basic pastry
directions: Cover with foil and bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Remove foil and bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: french sesame bread
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups flour, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add warm water to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl.
Add 1 cup flour and beat 2 minutes at high speed. Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Knead 4 to 5 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turn to grease top.
Cover and let rise until doubled (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down dough; divide into 3 balls.
Place on greased baking sheets which have been sprinkled with corn meal.
Make several gashes on top of each loaf.
Cover; let rise until doubled (about 1 hour).
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: confetti bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press crescent roll dough into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Mix cream cheese, mayo and garlic powder.
After crust cools, spread with cream cheese mixture.
Top with vegetables and sprinkle with Salad Supreme to taste.
Cut into squares and serve as an appetizer or hors d'oeuvres.

title: stir-fried beef with green onions
directions: Remove any fat or muscle from the beef and slice against the grain.
Shred finely and mix with 1 teaspoon rice wine, 1/2 tablespoon soy sauce, 1/2 tablespoon cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water.
Marinate for about 20 minutes.
Before stir-frying, add 1 tablespoon oil and toss lightly.
(The oil will prevent the shreds from sticking together during frying.)
Cut the green onion stalks into 1-inch sections.
If the stalks are thick, split in half lengthwise.
Heat pan and add 1/2 cup oil; heat until hot (about 275°).
Add the beef shreds and stir-fry over medium heat, using chopsticks or a spatula to separate the shreds.
When the meat changes color (about 20 seconds later), remove and drain.
Heat pan and add 3 tablespoons oil; heat until very hot.

Add the green onion sections and stir-fry for about 10 seconds until fragrant. Add the beef, 1 teaspoon rice wine, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, 1/4 teaspoon m.s.g., 1/2 teaspoon sugar, 1/8 teaspoon black pepper, 1/2 tablespoon cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water and toss lightly.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sesame oil over the stir-fried mixture (added for sheen).
Toss lightly and remove to a serving platter.

title: mixed fresh vegetables
directions: Wash vegetables.
Cut squash into 1-inch slices.
Cut onions and pepper into large slices.
If you use tomatoes, peel first. All vegetables should be in large slices to stay firm.
Pick a glass baking dish large enough to hold the amount of vegetables for the people you want to serve.
Toss vegetables with remaining ingredients, except onion rings.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and lemon rind.
Add eggs, one at a time, to creamed mixture.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture and stir gently.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in carrot, raisins, coconut and pecans.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, oil, apple and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir only until combined.
Spoon in muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Yield: 18 muffins.

title: cheese apples
directions: Drain apples and place in a buttered oblong baking dish. Combine sugar, margarine, flour and cheese. Mash over apples. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Mix sugars, oleo and peanut butter.
Add egg, milk, vanilla, flour, baking soda and salt.
Make into balls and roll in sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Add chocolate kiss and bake 5 minutes longer.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Gradually add milk, stirring all the time.
Pour in custard cups.
Place cups in a baking pan of hot water.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean. Cool.
Yields 6 servings.

title: poulet de normandy
directions: Mix stuffing and margarine melted in water and set aside. Combine onion, celery, mayonnaise and salt and mix well with bread mixture.

title: grace's easy-no knead rolls
directions: Mix
flour and Crisco like pastry, set aside.
Mix yeast and sugar
to
warm
water,
set
aside until it foams, about 3 minutes.
Whip
eggs, add to yeast mixture.
Blend all together slowly, add
more
flour
to
form a ball of dough.
It will be slightly soft.
Coat side of bowl and dough with butter.
Cover and set
to
rise once.
Punch down.
Roll out and shape or cut as desired,
coat
with
butter.
Place in pan or cookie sheet. Let rise.
Bake at 350° to 400° until brown.

title: beef boogie
directions: Cut up uncooked meat.
Add all ingredients except noodles. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over noodles.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soups and sour cream in large mixing bowl.
Add chicken and Veg-All.
Pour into 9 x 13 glass baker.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers over top.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; bake for 10 minutes or until crackers are toasted.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt shortening in a saucepan and stir in brown sugar.
Cool slightly.
Then add the eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts and bits and pour into a well-greased pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Brown meat and drain. Combine onion, cheese and peppers in a separate container.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved. Add buttermilk.
Chill.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill to set.

title: nanny's carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients together. Add all the wet ingredients. If desired, add chopped nuts. Pour into two 9-inch greased or sprayed and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: strawberry bavarian cream
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving syrup.
Pour boiling water over gelatin in bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add enough cold water to reserved syrup to measure 1 cup.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Chill until almost set.
In chilled bowl, beat cream until stiff. Beat gelatin until foamy. Fold gelatin and strawberries into whipped cream.
You can add other fruits.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
In larger bowl, combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix. Beat until mixture becomes creamy and smooth.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add in flour mixture, 1 cup at a time.
Stir in nuts (optional).
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 9 to 12 minutes.

title: cherry buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Set this aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine these ingredients:
warm water, eggs, salt, sugar, shortening, flour.
Mix and add dissolved yeast to above ingredients.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto a floured board.
Like making bread.
Place back in large bowl and cover with damp cloth.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and divide in half.
Roll out one of the halves and shape in rectangle (10 - 15 inches).
Butter dough and spread brown sugar and cinnamon on top.
Roll up in log shape.
Cut buns 1 1/2 inch wide.
Place in greased pan 9 x 13 inch laying the buns on their side.
Spoon Cherry Pie Filling on top of each bun.
Let rest 1/2 hour.
Bake at 375 degrees about 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: aunt ruby's brownies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut and remove from pan while warm.

title: holiday hideways
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Place dough in very thin layer around drained cherries.
Place 2 tablespoons apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet one minute.
Dip cookies in melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend well. Stir in pecans. Pour mixture into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy with 1 stick of margarine in double boiler.
Set aside.
Cream sugar with 1 stick of margarine.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour mixture.
Beat well after each.
Add nuts, vanilla and melted candy.
Pour into 10 or 12-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or longer, if needed.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in vanilla, apples and pecans.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: hot or cold chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with crushed rice crispies or corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie 1
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Put margarine in pan and melt.
Heat milk in microwave until room temperature and beat in egg yolks.
Put flour mixture in pan with margarine, pour in milk mixture slowly.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add vanilla and put in baked pie crust.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter in saucepan until golden.
Add mushrooms; cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Blend in flour, paprika, salt, basil and thyme.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in chicken broth and wine.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles, 1 minute.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream. Add chicken, lemon juice and dill.
Heat thoroughly over low heat, but do not boil.
Serve over noodles.

title: jeri's italian beef
directions: Cut through the meat (but not completely) to let flavor cook through.
Put everything into the crock-pot.
When the meat is done, pull apart with roasting fork.
Leave meat in the juices. Serve with slotted spoon onto sliced Avanti's or Kroger's sweet Italian bread.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix all together.
Put into two pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done in middle.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Put water and cubes in a 4-quart Dutch oven over high heat. While liquid comes to a boil, stir in onions, tomato paste and paprika.
When liquid returns to a boil, stir in pasta.
Pull off chicken skin with a paper towel.
Add chicken to pot.
Let mixture boil about 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes, until chicken is tender.

title: biscotti croccanti
directions: Butter and flour 2 cookie sheets.
Preheat oven at 350°. Leave almonds for last.
Put all other ingredients in a bowl, mix and knead to form a soft dough.
Add almonds and kneed.
Divide dough in 4 parts.
Makes 4 loaves, 1/2-inch high.
Bake until golden.
Cool.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Chill 1 hour. Heat oven to 375°.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
While warm frost with Burnt Butter Glaze.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, onion and pepper in cold water for 20 minutes with 2 tablespoons salt.
Drain.
Make vinegar solution of sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over cukes.

title: dominosaurus pound cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl; set aside.
In separate bowl, cream butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk.
Line outside of 9 or 9 1/2-inch spring-form cake pan with foil.
Grease and flour pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan.
To prevent crumbling, freeze cake 45 minutes before cutting.
Makes 8 servings.
Frost with Buttercream Frosting.

title: cherry fudge cobbler
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in the pie filling.
Pour dry brownie mix over top of pie filling.
Drizzle melted margarine all over top of brownie mix evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: crowd pleasing potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Add all ingredients, except corn flakes and melted margarine.
Blend thoroughly and put in buttered casserole dish.
Use Pam for less calories.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix with other ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or microwave on High for 10 minutes.

title: church windows
directions: In a large bowl, mix Funmallows, coconut and nuts in bowl; set aside.
Melt morsels and butter until chocolate is smooth.
Beat egg into mixture until smooth.
Have 2 sheets of wax (one each) paper and aluminum foil about 2 feet long.
Mix the mixture until chocolate covers all.
Lay wax paper on table and pour mixture onto paper.
Mold into about an 18-inch log.
Takes special handling somewhat to get it that way, so take it easy.
Now, use the foil to cover log and put in the fridge until next day.

title: sugar-free lemonade pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Crust: Mix graham crackers with 1 1/2 teaspoons NutraSweet, then cut in margarine and press crumbs into 2 pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes or until lightly browned.
Then cool.

title: stuffed pepper slices
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; remove seeds, wash and drain.
Cream cottage cheese in blender (thin with milk if necessary); remove. Add pimento, parsley, chives, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Soak gelatin in cold water; dissolve completely over simmering water. Add to cheese mixture.
Fill peppers with mixture; chill in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Cut each pepper into 4 thick rings. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter; add sugar and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Pour into crusts and chill in freezer.
Makes 2 pies.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix all together and put into a well oiled mold.
Should set for several hours or overnight.

title: lemon sauce(for bread pudding or pound cake)
directions: Mix
sugar and cornstarch, add boiling water gradually; stirring
until
smooth.
Cook 5 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly on medium heat.	Add butter, salt, lemon juice and lemon
rind.
A little yellow food color may be added, if desired. Spoon over pound cake slices or bread pudding.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Brown meat in shortening; add onions and saute until tender. Add water and simmer, covered, for 50 minutes.
Layer meat in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer thinly sliced potatoes over.
Mix together the soup, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese and cornflake crumbs and bake an additional 1/2 hour.

title: easy pork chops with gravy
directions: Trim off fat on chops.
Salt and pepper them and brown them in pan.
Remove chops and place in glass baking dish.
Cut onion into slices and place on top of chops.
Mix soup, catsup and Worcestershire sauce together.
Pour over chops.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: beer - cheese soup
directions: Combine beer and stock base in 3-quart saucepan; stir over medium-high heat until stock base is dissolved.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Blend 1 1/2 cups milk with flour in medium bowl.
Gradually stir into soup, blending well.
Add remaining milk and cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, about 15 minutes.
Blend in cheese, a little at a time, stirring until melted.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Ladle soup into individual bowls and serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk until soft ball forms in hot water.
This takes some time.
Add dates and let cook until dates are soft. Add pecans and beat until stiff.
Roll in a wet cloth, chill and slice.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef in oleo.
Add onion.
Saute a few minutes before adding mushrooms, then add beef bouillon soup.
Let this simmer for awhile.
Stir flour into sour cream.
Add sour cream to beef mixture.
Serve Stroganoff over noodles or rice.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Cook meat and drain fat.
Add all ingredients, except biscuits and cheese.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Press biscuits into greased muffin pans.
Add meat mix and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400° until golden brown.

title: teriyaki winger dingers
directions: Meat:
Recipe is for chicken wings, but recipe also works well for other cuts of chicken or you can slice beef into thin strips and skewer.
For wings, plan on 2 to 3 pounds for 4 to 6 people.

title: potato spinach puff
directions: Combine all except eggs. Blend in 4 egg yolks.
Beat 4 whites until stiff. Fold into mixture.
Pile lightly into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° until golden, about 40 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Empty pie filling into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Crumble dry cake mix on top of filling.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until bubbly and slightly brown.

title: sweet and sour pork (or chicken)
directions: Heat a heavy pan or electric skillet.
Add oil and heat.
Add pork and cook over high heat, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Cover, turn heat to medium and cook 5 minutes.
Uncover; add green pepper and cook 2 minutes.
Add tomato and pineapple chunks; cook for 1 minute.
Add water chestnuts.
Meanwhile, you have put the cornstarch in a little bowl, added the soy sauce, vinegar and water and mixed them well.
Add this mixture to the pot and cook, stirring, until thickened.
This recipe will probably be enough for only 3 or 4, so double it for 6 or 8, and serve with rice.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Mix as	listed.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.	Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Thaw
lemonade and use full strength.
Mix lemonade and milk well;
fold
into Cool Whip until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into pie
crusts
and refrigerate.
Sprinkle tops with grated chocolate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, sugar and cheese until soft.
Add Cool Whip.
Add ice cream a little at a time.
Move quickly so that ice cream does not melt too much.
Makes 2 pies.
Put in freezer.

title: baked couscous with spinach and cashews
directions: Combine the couscous, boiling stock or water and salt in a large bowl; cover with a plate.
Let sit 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork.

title: chicken strips
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Dip strips in melted butter, then roll in crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn once after 15 minutes.
Dip in favorite sauce.

title: 1-2-3 casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add mushroom soup and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Add corn.
Simmer until corn is hot and well coated with soup mix. Serve with green salad and French bread.

title: cornbread dressing(may be halved)
directions: In large bowl, put cornmeal.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to cornmeal.
Add onion and beaten eggs.
Add enough buttermilk to make a soft but not thin batter.
Add celery.
Pour into large greased baking dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Take out of oven; pour broth in while tearing dressing with potato masher. Add enough broth to make a very soft batter.
Add sage, thyme, black pepper and chicken parts, boiled, boned and chopped.
Pour into large greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: herbed beer bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, cheese and seasoning.
Mix well.
Stir in beer to produce thick batter.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix
well.
Roll
in balls and bake on greased, floured pan at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: In a large pan, brown both ground chuck and sausage.
Melt Velveeta cheese into the meat mixture.
Add taco seasoning. Serve with nacho chips.

title: baked corn pudding for 6
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, beating well. Stir in corn and milk.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Stir once halfway through cooking.
When done a silver knife inserted will come out clean.
Mixture can be prepared ahead and stored in refrigerator in a jar (shake well).

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix crushed crackers and margarine together and sprinkle over chicken mixture. Sprinkle with poppy seed and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baba ghanoozh-eggplant dipp
directions: Steam eggplant or bake in oven for 40 minutes until soft. Peel, mash; add salt, garlic, lemon juice and tahini.
Garnish with fresh chopped parsley.

title: patio chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour over chicken and let stand until ready to barbecue.
Cook slowly on grill for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa; blend in melted butter, milk and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts; pour into greased pan.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Soak cucumbers 3 days in water to cover.
Add 2 cups salt to water for soaking cucumbers.
Drain water and rinse cucumbers.
Mix alum with clear water; add pickles and soak 1 day.
Rinse well.
Make syrup of vinegar, sugar and pickling spices (tied in a bag).
Return cucumbers to syrup and boil 1 hour.
Seal in jars.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Combine oil, lemon, oregano and garlic powder.
Brush on chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover; brush again with lemon mixture.
Continue for 20 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika. Serves 2 to 4.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine crabmeat, eggs, mayonnaise and dry mustard.
Spread on croissants; sprinkle with dill.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: angel hair pasta salad
directions: 1. Cook the pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse under cold water. 2. Mix together the pasta, shrimp, green onions and ranch dressing, then carefully work the shrimp into the pasta with your hands.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and melted butter.
Then add rice and milk.
Mix in raisins.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange ice
directions: Add orange juice, water and sugar to blender jar.
Cover and blend at crush ice speed for 5 seconds.
With blender running at crush ice speed, add ice cubes through lid, insert 2 to 3 at a time.
Blend until thick and smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Turn off and stir down mixture frequently, 7 to 8 times.
(This helps blend the ice evenly.)
Serve immediately.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch and set aside. Combine vanilla, salt, eggs and milk. Combine the 2 mixtures and add margarine.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Buttermilk can be made by putting 1 tablespoon of white vinegar in a measuring cup and then adding milk to the 1-cup mark. Let sit for about 3 minutes; stir and use.

title: dinosaur bread
directions: Trace the shape of any dinosaur onto foil lined cookie sheet. Spray with Pam.
Open can(s) of biscuits and divide each one in half.
Dip into butter and roll into cinnamon and sugar mixture. Place biscuits on foil to make the shape of dinosaur.
Add raisins for eye and other features.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: biscuit and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic powder.
Simmer.
Cut biscuits in half and press in the bottom of a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in a greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
While cake is hot, combine 1 1/2 cups confectioners sugar, 1/4 cup water and 5 tablespoons lemon juice.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Spoon over warm cake.

title: fruit crisp
directions: *Can also use other fruits such as raspberries, blackberries, peaches and apples.

title: razzle dazzle(cereal snack or candy)
directions: Bring corn syrup, sugar and milk to a boil.
Cook to firm ball stage or 236°.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Add vanilla.
Pour over cereal mixture; mix thoroughly.
Pour onto wax paper to cool.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix chopped pecans, flour and margarine well.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese with sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Pour blueberry pie filling over this. Refrigerate for several hours overnight.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Immediately, when removing from oven, punch cake full of holes.
Pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk over top.
Pour 1 jar caramel ice cream topping over this.
Let cool.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with shredded Heath bars.
Chill.

title: barbara's stew
directions: Good for a crowd.
Use a large roaster, it's best.

title: trembleque (coconut custard)
directions: Combine milk, salt, sugar and cinnamon in pan.
Dissolve cornstarch in part of the milk and add it to the rest of the mixture.
Cook on medium heat, stirring at all times, until the mixture thickens.
Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes more, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Take off stove and transfer to a shallow sheet.
Cool 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: coca-cola roast
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Braise roast thoroughly in saucepan; mix chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and Coke.
Mix well. Place roast in large roasting bag; add carrots, potatoes and onions on top of roast.
Add liquid ingredients.
Seal.
Make 3 small slits in top of bag.
Bake 3 hours or until tender.

title: mrs. artie's peanut brittle
directions: Bring 1/2 cup water to boil.
Then add 2 cups sugar and 1 cup white
syrup.
Stir
until	dissolved
and boil until it will spin a
thread.	Add
2	cups raw peanuts and cook slowly over low fire until
it turns a golden brown.
Take from fire and add 2 tablespoons
butter,
2 teaspoons baking soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir
quickly.
Spread
on two large cookie sheets that have
been	well
buttered.
Place	in cold area. Break into pieces when cold.

title: low-fat buttermilk caramels
directions: Mix sugar, buttermilk, and Karo in large pan, 4-quart or larger.
Bring to a boil (it boils high).
Add soda and cook until soft to firm ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla. Beat until it loses its glaze.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Add onion to vegetables; cook according to package directions. Drain.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add vegetables and rest of ingredients.
Cook until thoroughly heated.

title: saucy beef over rice
directions: You will need 1 large Reynold's oven bag.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in oven bag.
Place bag in oven dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Add undrained tomatoes, soup mix, water and pepper to the bag.
Squeeze bag to mix ingredients.
Add beef tips to bag.
Turn bag to cover and coat tips.
Close bag with tie and cut slit in bag on top.
Bake until tender 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bow tie pasta with vegetables
directions: Saute garlic in oil until soft.
Add remaining vegetables (except peas) and seasonings.
Toss well to coat.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes approximately 1 quart.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Beat eggs, stir in milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Dip bread in above mixture and fry in butter until brown.
Top with powdered sugar.

title: peach parfait pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water in 2-quart saucepan.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened, but not set (15 to 20 minutes).
Fold in drained peaches.
Turn into pie shell.
Chill until firm (20 to 25 minutes).
Garnish with whipped cream and additional peaches, if desired.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan. Add sugar and cocoa. (Mix these 2 before adding.) Add milk, eggs and vanilla and stir well. Pour in unbaked pie shell.	Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes, until crust is brown and pie sets or toothpick comes out clean when put in center of pie.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, milk, crumbs, ketchup and salt in bowl.
Shape into loaf; place in middle of a 13 x 2 x 2-inch pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place vegetables in layers around loaf.
Mix the dried parsley flakes, 1 teaspoon salt and a few grains of pepper. Sprinkle this mixture over the vegetables.
Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil; bake until vegetables are done.
Uncover; bake 10 more minutes to brown meat.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: judged as favorite pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta (add 1 tablespoon oil to water to prevent boiling over).
While pasta cooks, cut up vegetables, eggs and meat.
When you add other ingredients to cooked pasta, let eggs be last to put into bowl.
Liberally sprinkle any spices you have that compliment salads.
Stir all ingredients and add mayonnaise.
Chill overnight if possible.
Keeps up to two weeks in refrigerator and gets better as it ages.
Store in airtight container.

title: easy casserole
directions: Place meat in buttered casserole.
Add soup and water.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet-n-sour mustard sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly together.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt; bring to full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly, over moderate heat.
Add chocolate morsels and semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is well blended.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla extract.
Pour into aluminum or glass 8-inch square pan.
Chill in refrigerator until firm (about 2 hours).

title: ocean garden spaghetti
directions: Drain tuna.
In large skillet saute onion, garlic, broccoli, mushrooms and oregano in oil and margarine until crisp and tender. Cut zucchini into 1/4 x 2-inch sticks.
Cut tomato into eighths. Add to skillet with veggies and cook until zucchini is tender. Break tuna into chunks and add to veggies.
Heat through.
Keep warm.

title: mashed potato soup
directions: Saute carrot and onion in melted butter.
Add balance of ingredients and cook for about 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
For richer flavor, add the chicken or beef bouillon.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Blend together the Eagle Brand milk and 2 thawed lemonade. Fold in 13 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Thoroughly beat together pulp, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then cooking oil.
Bake in square pan or 2 small loaf pans at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Melt butter; add milk and cool.
When cool, add beaten egg and flour.
Stir well with spoon or fork.
I mix with my hands. Divide into 4 balls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill.
When well chilled, roll out each ball and cut into 2-inch squares.
Place in layers on cookie sheet and freeze.
Place wax paper between layers.
When frozen, place in plastic bag and seal, then return to freezer until ready to use.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce. Add pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set and stir in nuts.
Pour into 11 x 7 x 2 dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: jam nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake until well done.
Makes 3 layers.
For fruit cake, add 1 jar candied fruits to cake batter.

title: brown rice
directions: Cook, covered, on 1-quart casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Combine in a saucepan cherry pie filling, sugar, pineapple, cornstarch and red food coloring.
Cook on medium heat until thick. Remove from heat and add gelatin and allow to cool; add bananas and pecans.
Pour into pie shells, top with Cool Whip or whipped cream. Chill.

title: pasta carbonnara
directions: Cook bacon and saute onion and pepper in same pan, along with the bacon.
At the same time, cook pasta according to directions on bag.
Beat eggs in separate bowl; set aside until pasta is cooked.
Drain pasta and put in casserole dish.
Take bacon, onion and pepper mixture and toss together.
Next, pour beaten egg mixture over pasta and make sure all is well coated.
Put cover on dish and let sit for 1 minute or two, then serve.

title: chewy bars
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Press
into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle nuts, chocolate chips and
coconut over crumbs (amount vary according to ones taste).
Last pour milk
over
all.
Bake at
for 25 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat it until fluffy.
Mash bananas and add to egg mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Add flour, baking powder and salt after you've sifted it together a little at a time.
Pour into well greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole(microwave dinner)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, crumble beef; add onion.
Cook 5 minutes on High; stir 3 times.
Drain excess fat.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in beans and soup.
Set aside.
In bowl, measure water and butter for potatoes as called for on package.
Omit milk.
Cover and cook on High 3 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in potato buds.
Add egg; season.
Set aside.
Cook casserole (1st mixture), covered, for 7 minutes on 70%.
Stir.
Spoon potatoes on top in mounds.
Cover; cook on High 2 1/2 minutes until potatoes are hot.
Top potatoes with cheese.
Cook, uncovered, until cheese melts (30 seconds).
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: flowerpot surprise
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Crush Oreo cookies.
Place 1/2 of cookie mix in bottom of an 8-inch flowerpot.
Fill with pudding mixture; top with remaining cookies.
Add silk flowers and you have your surprise.

title: 1-2-3-4 fruit dressing
directions: Combine in saucepan juice from lemon and orange.
Add egg and sugar; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until boiling. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
In saucepan, melt butter; remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk. Heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens a little and is smooth.
Add most of the cheese (save some for the top).
Heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Combine cooked macaroni with sauce in a 2-quart casserole, top with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° about 20 to 25 minutes or until nicely browned and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: marshmallow sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks separately with 1 cup sugar.
Add orange juice and beat 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to egg whites and beat until stiff and then add together.
Add flour carefully.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes in tube pan.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, molasses and hot water.
Stir in soda, egg and spices.
Gradually add the flour until well mixed. Let dough stand overnight in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
Drop by spoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes, checking often.

title: hominy
directions: Pour juice off hominy.
Add soup, chilies and 1 cup of cheese to hominy in casserole bowl.
Mix.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion, peppers, sugar, salt and vinegar in a large kettle.
Cook, stirring frequently, over low heat until thick.
Pour into hot sterilized pint jars.
Place hot lids and rings on jars, screwing rings on tight.
Yields 6 pints.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Roast pork at 375° for 2 1/2 hours until done.
Cool slightly and shred pork.
Mix all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over shredded pork.
Freeze, if desired.
Heat up in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands until small balls stick together and stay in a ball.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Make small balls about 1-inch in diameter and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
These cheese balls can be frozen and baked later.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with a single layer of vanilla wafers.
Next, put 1 layer of sliced bananas.
Continue layering vanilla wafers and bananas until you reach the top of the bowl, leaving the top layer as bananas.

title: the best fruit cake bread ever
directions: In a bowl, combine nuts, cherries, dates, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and flour.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves or 5 small loaves.

title: squash supreme
directions: Mash squash; add sour cream, carrot, onion, soup, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle a layer of bread crumbs in shallow casserole dish.
Spoon squash mixture over crumbs.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, onion and raisins in medium bowl and set aside.
In small bowl, combine mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well with spoon.
Pour over ingredients in medium bowl and mix. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce with first 5 ingredients.
Put half of the potatoes into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half the onion and half the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Uncover and continue to bake until top is browned.

title: black cow
directions: Blend the package of Oreo cookies in blender.
Set aside 1 cup of crumbs.
Melt margarine and mix with cookie crumbs.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough water to make 4 cups.
Heat 2 cups of the water and pineapple juice to boiling and dissolve jello.
Add remaining liquid and cool until it begins to set.
Mix the cream cheese with mixer and add jello to cheese.
Mix well. Add pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Fold in
Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool for 2 hours.

title: lasagne
directions: Dice prosage and brown slowly in large, electric skillet or frypan.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray.
Mix ingredients (except chicken) together in bottom of roaster.
Put chicken on top; cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.
May also use pork chops.

title: steak casserole
directions: Brown meat. Drain off any grease.
Mix all ingredients together and cover casserole. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Can be cooked in crock-pot.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs, flour, soda and salt. Mix well. Add chopped apples, pecans and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in angel food cake pan.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and lemon juice; boil for 2 minutes. Soak gelatin in cold water; then add to hot mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine beans, onions and peppers.
Combine dressing and sugar.
Pour over bean mixture and toss.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crumble cookies until fine.
Put 3/4 of bag into bowl and spread to form a crust.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar until smooth.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Cream the sugar, salad dressing and cocoa together.
Mix flour with baking soda.
Add vanilla to water, then add alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes for round pans or 40 minutes for square pan.
Cool, then ice as desired.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir gently.
Pour mixture into a small jar (a baby food jar works great).
Dip the end of a plastic straw into bubble solution.
Pull it out and let it drip once.
Blow through the other end of the straw, and you've got bubbles.

title: heart of chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Put into softened shortening.
Add 1 cup milk until mixed.
Beat 2 minutes on low speed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 2 layer pans, greased and floured, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Fill layers; cover with any chocolate icing.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Stir this into batter.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Very moist.
Frost with Coca-Cola Frosting while warm.

title: ice cream
directions: In large bowl, mix Eagle Brand and Carnation.
Add eggs; beat until blended well.
Add sugar and beat until foamy.
Add vanilla and pour into freezer.
Add milk to fill freezer.
Start freezer. Should be ready in about 30 minutes.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; the only liquid is the pineapple juice. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Chill for at least 6 hours before serving.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Let strawberries stand while preparing other ingredients. Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water for 5 minutes; dissolve over boiling water and add crushed berries.
Mix thoroughly.
Set aside to chill.
When it begins to thicken, fold in whipped cream.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Stir in sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Spoon the batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle miniature marshmallows on warm cake. Turn oven off and put cake in oven until marshmallows melt.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans in pot of cold water overnight.
Cook beans
next day for 20 minutes, then pour into a large roasting pan.
Add bacon cut into pieces, can of tomato juice, Karo syrup, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Bake in oven at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until soft.

title: dan's fluffy pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Spoon onto hot griddle. Turn once.
Serve with gobs of butter and maple syrup.
Makes 12.

title: ambrosia cheesecake
directions: Day Before Serving:
Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine coconut, almonds and butter; mix well.
Press mixture into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake until golden, about 15 minutes. Cool.
In large bowl of electric mixer, at high speed, beat cream cheese, sugar, flour, orange peel and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in apricot nectar and cream of coconut.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Stir in pineapple; pour into prepared crust.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until set.
Cool in pan on wire rack; refrigerate overnight.

title: bear with sour cream
directions: Trim most of the fat from the chops.
Season with garlic salt, parsley flakes and black pepper.
Fry bacon and brown the chops in the fat.
Remove the meat to a baking pan and add 1/2 cup water, sour cream, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and the bay leaf.
Bring to a boil and pour over the chops.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours.

title: hearty macaroni stew
directions: Cut the steaks and bell peppers into 1-inch pieces. Saute in the vegetable oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat until steak is browned.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add beaten eggs. Mix well. Sift dry ingredients. Mix all together until smooth. Add rest of ingredients. Drop onto a greased cookie sheet with a teaspoon. Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: back home's cornbread salad
directions: In a large bowl, break up corn muffins.
Add mayonnaise, green pepper, onion and celery.
Fold in tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Cut bacon into small pieces.
Fry until crisp.
Drain. Sprinkle over top of salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crab meat) very well.
I use the mixer.
Stir in crab meat.
Place in 2-quart dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: healthy potato bacon soup(low-fat)
directions: Spray 3-quart saucepan with nonstick spray. Add onions and bacon.
Cook until tender. Stir in water and potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes until potatoes are just tender.
Using a fork, slightly mash some of the potatoes. Stir in evaporated milk, Butter Buds and pepper.
Heat through. Do not boil.

title: slovakian crispies (chrusciky)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt into a bowl.
Cut in the shortening (as for pie crust).
Add the eggs, milk.
Mix and knead until smooth.
Turn out upon floured board.
Roll very thin.
Cut into strips (5 x 1 in.) with a slit in the center lengthwise.
Pull an end through slit and up as a twist.
Heat fat in a deep kettle. Fry to a golden brown, 1 minute, watching carefully.
Remove on absorbent paper.
Dust with confectioners' sugar.

title: buttermilk white cake(this is a favorite with my family.)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cream the shortening and sugar well. Add eggs alternating with milk to dry ingredients.
Beat well after each cup full.
Pour into 9-inch pans, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes. This cake is very light so be careful getting it out of the pans.
If you use a 13 x 9-inch pan, increase baking time to 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Ice with Seven Minute Icing.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix together all dry ingredients except for 1/2 cup of flour which you will add to raisins.
Mix all together, except for egg whites and raisins.
After mixing well, fold in egg whites, then fold in raisins.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done.
Makes 3 layers.

title: summer pot roast
directions: In
4 quart
Dutch
oven,
cook
roast	until
browned. Remove meat.
Cook
onion	5
minutes.
Stir
in flour and add beer, water and
bouillon
until thickened.
Add sugar, thyme, salt, pepper, garlic, bay leaf and meat.	Heat to boiling and reduce to low.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add celery and carrots last 15 minutes.

title: jumbo fruited oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter in large bowl until creamy. Blend in eggs, apple juice concentrate and vanilla.
Add flour, oats, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and allspice; mix well.
Stir in dried fruit and nuts.
Drop scant 1/4 cupfuls of dough, 3 inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheets; flatten slightly.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheets; transfer to wire rack to cool completely. Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen jumbo cookies.

title: junkyard salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Beat the 2 cups sugar, eggs and margarine until fluffy (real fluffy).
Combine the flour and baking powder.
Alternate flour mixture into egg mixture with the sour cream.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon and set aside.
Pour half the cake mixture into a tube pan.
Pour the cinnamon and sugar around cake mixture.
Cut into cake mixture as to marble.
Place sliced apples around cake. Pour balance of mixture.
Repeat.
Pour remaining cinnamon on top to create crisp crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour; 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, then continue until finished at 325°.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and water.
Over medium heat, bring just to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted and smooth.
Add vanilla. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour, baking soda and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 16.
These freeze well.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: In a dutch oven or soup kettle, brown ground beef and onion until done; drain.
Stir in the remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until pasta is tender. Yield:
12 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add sugar to oil and eggs; mix well.
Add all other ingredients; stir until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: double toffee delight coffee cake
directions: Beat 2 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with 1/2 of the sugar and nut mixture.
Pour remaining batter over brown sugar and cover with remaining sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until top springs back when touched.

title: bean bake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: miss nell callis' dark fruit cake
directions: Cut up all fruit together; add coconut, pineapple, sweet cherries and mincemeat.
Let stand in fridge overnight.
Next day, mix cake ingredients as usual.
In a very large pan, stir the fruit into cake mixture.
Grease and line with wax or brown paper 2 medium tube cake pans and one loaf pan.
Cook at 300° with a shallow pan of water in oven (keep water in this at all times) for 2 to 3 hours.
Keep testing for doneness.

title: fruit ice pops
directions: In an electric blender or food processor, blend the strawberries, pineapple and corn syrup together until pureed, about 1 minute.
Pour into 4 (5 ounce) paper cups.
Freeze until partly set.
Into each cup, insert 2 flat popsicle sticks, placing each on opposite sides halfway between center and edge.
Freeze until firm. Peel off paper and cut each pop in half between sticks.
Makes 8 servings.

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and peaks form. Fold in batter.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Spread Toasted Coconut Topping over cake.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Mix all together and serve with crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Chop bell pepper and onion and saute in margarine.
Mix corn, eggs (slightly beaten), rice, bell pepper and onion together. Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: sweet potato crisp
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, 3/4 cup butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in mixer until creamy.
Combine brown sugar and flour; add 3/4 cup melted butter.
Add pecans.
Place potato mixture in large casserole; cover with brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° until heated thoroughly.
Serves approximately 15 people.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together except cake mix, butter and
pecans.
Crumble
cake mix on top of pumpkin mixture.
Pour
melted
butter evenly over cake mix and then sprinkle on nuts.
Bake
1 hour or until set at 350°. Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In a large saucepan, combine 2 cups sugar and milk.
Cook on low heat.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion, salt and pepper until tender.
Drain off excess water; add margarine.
Place in casserole dish:
1 layer of squash, 1 layer of stuffing and 1 layer of cheese.
Repeat layers. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Combine cheese, butter, flour and paprika in bowl; mix well. Shape 1 tablespoon mixture around each olive.
Store in freezer. Arrange on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden.

title: colorful veggie bake
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package directions. Drain. Place half in an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. In a small saucepan, combine cheese and 4 tablespoons butter. Cook and stir over low heat until melted. Pour half over vegetables. Repeat layers. Melt the remaining butter. Toss with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over the top. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 8 to 10 servings. Enjoy.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Cook on medium heat until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Let cool for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal; stir well.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper; let cool.

title: caramel frosting or quick fudge
directions: Cook all ingredients together (except confectioners sugar and vanilla) for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm. Add confectioners sugar and vanilla and beat until creamy and thick enough to spread.

title: peach blossom roll
directions: Lightly grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with wax paper.
Grease paper.

title: sausage(for macaroni sauce)
directions: Bake
covered
in large baking pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut
into
pieces
before
putting
in tomato sauce. (Poke small holes in sausage with fork before baking.)

title: lime sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Mix well the lime and water in large crock or container - do not use aluminum - add cucumbers and soak for 24 hours.
Drain, rinse and wash well - handle carefully.
Cover with cold water and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain and cover with hot brine made of remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes and seal in hot jars.
Makes 4 or 5 qts.
If you have lime left over from this year's pickles, do not use next year.
It is the fresh lime that makes the crispness.

title: fresh strawberry pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.
Cool completely, overnight if possible.
Bake 2 pie crusts.
Fill with fresh strawberries. Pour cool filling over berries.
Top with whipped topping.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Peel and chop potatoes in 1/2 to 1-inch squares.
Arrange potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole in 3 layers, topping each layer with a dash of pepper and 1/3 each of salt, parsley, onion and cheese.
Dot with margarine and pour half and half over potatoes.
Cover and cook in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes longer.

title: coconut or banana pie
directions: Separate egg yolks and egg whites.
Mix yolks, cornstarch, vanilla and sugar.
Slowly add milk and cook until thick.

title: sumptuous meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Fry and crumble bacon.
Chop red onion.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients, except unbeaten egg and milk, together with a pastry blender.
Pour milk into mixture slowly and add egg last.
Knead only five times on a floured board.
More will make biscuits heavy.
Cut with 2-inch round cutter.
Bake at 450° for about 12 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Freeze can of soup.
After frozen, take out and open can. Shave out with a fork into cream cheese (add lemon if desired). Serve chilled with chips.

title: baked spinach balls
directions: Stir together above ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and freeze.
Bake the frozen balls on a cookie sheet with sides for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 50.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix bread and seasonings together.
