Saute celery, onion and apples in butter in large skillet.
Add to bread mixture along with broth, meat and eggs.
Toss until all moistened, if needed.
Add more broth or water, enough for 12 to 14 pound turkey or bake separately in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Set
aside
cup
cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, butter
and
1 egg in a large mixing bowl.	Mix with fork until crumbly.
Press
crumbs in a greased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake
at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Combine reserved cake mix, 3 eggs, brown sugar, Karo and vanilla in a mixing bowl.	Beat at medium speed for 1 to 2
minutes.
Pour
over partially baked crust and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: cheesy chicken bake
directions: Combine cereal, soup, cheese, celery, onion, 1/2 cup cereal, milk and pepper.
Mix well.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish (spray dish with Pam or Mazola).
Combine rest of cereal and melted butter.
Spread over top.
Bake at 375° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
(Cereal topping will be lightly browned and casserole will be bubbly.) Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: beef with noodles
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add chopped onions and meat cut into strips.
Cook until brown.
Add bell pepper strips and cook until down.
Add grated carrot and soy sauce to taste.
Heat through. Serve with noodles or over rice, if desired.

title: cherries in snow
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar and beat some more.
By hand, fold in crackers, vanilla and nuts. Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip. Add cherries and chill thoroughly.
You may add your favorite topping.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add chicken (skinned and cut in large pieces).
Cook until browned (10 to 12 minutes).
Salt and pepper. Arrange chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add mushrooms to skillet and saute 3 minutes.
Scatter mushrooms over chicken and pour chicken broth over all.
Cover; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Start with quarter inch round steak, cut into serving size pieces.
Use carpenter type hammer and pound heavily on both sides.
Stick under cold water and get real wet.
Flour very heavily.
Place in skillet with cooking oil and fry at high temperature, turning only one time.
Salt and pepper to taste.
If this is done right, the steak will melt in your mouth.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, sugar and barbecue sauce. Separate biscuits and press into cupcake pans.
Pull up on sides. Spoon meat mix into biscuits; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until brown and biscuits are cooked.

title: fresh corn soup
directions: Saute garlic and onions in oil.
Add shrimp and shrimp juice. Combine corn and simmer until tender.
Season salt and ajinomoto. Add young pepper leaves 3 minutes before removing from fire.

title: sugar-free lemon cheese cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, whip the cheeses until smooth. Add Equal and lemon rind.
In a separate bowl, mix lemon juice and eggs until smooth. Add egg mixture slowly, one cup at a time.
Mix well. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: old favorite apple cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar and add well beaten eggs. Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients with creamed mixture and add apples and nuts.
Mix all together well and turn into a slightly greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 -40 minutes.
Sprinkle with brown sugar last 10 minutes of baking.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine and peanut butter until smooth (about 1 minute).
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt; stir in 1 cup of chocolate morsels.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Immediately sprinkle remaining morsels over top of layer; wait 5 minutes and spread. Cool and cut into bars.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Combine vanilla wafer crumbs, nuts and milk; mix well.
Add raisins and cherries or pineapple.
Roll in waxed paper and chill well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel, cook and drain potatoes. Mash well and add other ingredients. Grease 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. May be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated or frozen. Thaw before baking.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce with cooked ground beef.
In casserole dish, place layer of meat mixture, a layer of noodles, layer of pepperoni ending with layer of cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cecilia's applesauce cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Combine oil and sugar. Stir in applesauce.
Add the dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then 15 minutes at 375°.

title: three generation chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and place in large pot.
Cover with salted water.
Bring to boil.
Cook chicken until tender.
While chicken is cooking, make dumplings.

title: chicken and rice cacciatore
directions: Cook and stir chicken with onion, green pepper and garlic in hot butter in large skillet until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: oriental salad
directions: (This dressing will keep in the fridge but will get very thick, just put it in the microwave for 10 to 20 seconds.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce.
Stir until most of it has melted.
Cool until it starts to jell.
Add apples, celery and nuts.
Chill.

title: beets with pineapple
directions: Drain beets.
Add pineapple and juice, sugar, salt, cornstarch, butter and lemon.
Cook on medium until thick.

title: big boy's strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pat into pie plate. Bake at 400° until brown (about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oriental grilled chicken(serves 4 to 5 people)
directions: Trim off the fat from chicken.
In a shallow bowl, combine lemon juice, honey, soy sauce and oil together.
Press the ginger and garlic through press and add to mixture in the bowl.
Dip chicken in seasoning mixture.
Fold scallion in half and roll one up in each thigh.
Secure with toothpick.
Grill or broil chicken (with medium heat) for 15 to 25 minutes, turning frequently, and basting with seasoning mixture, until cooked through.

title: couscous salad
directions: Mix all together and toss with the salad dressing.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring cocoa, water, margarine and salt to rolling boil; remove from stove.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Pour 1/4 cup melted butter into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Add 5 cups of frozen hash browns. Mix soup, sour cream, milk and green onions in separate bowl.
pour 1/2 mixture over hash browns. Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese on top. Add remainder of hash browns and mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Then cover with covered corn flakes.
Drizzle 2 Tbsp. melted butter on top. Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: talerini
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
When done drain.
Fry onions, garlic, and celery in oil.
When brown add hamburger and brown. Add sauces.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Pour into the cooked noodles.
Add the corn and the olives.
Mix well.
Put into a 13 x 9 inch glass dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° until brown.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Mix
all together; add flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise then roll out and cut.
Let rise again.
Fry in shortening at 350°.

title: old fashion spice cake
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift with other dry ingredients.
Add 2 tablespoons milk.
Add egg and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with remaining milk.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until cake tests done.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: apple-stuffed sausage patties
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sausage and beef; shape into ten 1/4-inch thick patties.
Spray saucepan with vegetable spray; add celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add juice; stir in stuffing mix, apple, parsley, mustard and pepper. Place about 1/4 cup stuffing atop each of 5 patties, spreading to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Top each with remaining 5 patties, pressing meat around edges to seal.

title: cheesy "spam" bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook sliced potatoes in boiling salted water 15 minutes.
Drain potatoes, saving 1 cup of cooking liquid. Place potatoes in casserole dish.

title: could be bojangles' biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender.
Blend in sour cream.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Handle gently and make into a ball. Pat out.
Cut.
Place in a baking pan.
Dribble with a squeeze butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: scallops scampi
directions: In large skillet, heat vegetable oil and butter.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute.
Add scallops, toss and saute until opaque, 3 to 4 minutes.
Drizzle with lemon juice and sprinkle with parsley. Serves 4.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and 1 chopped onion.
Add rest of ingredients and cook on low for 1 hour.
Serve with corn chips, grated cheese and sour cream.

title: nippy shrimp
directions: Combine shrimp and garlic.
Pour chili sauce over.
Cover; refrigerate several hours, stirring occasionally.
Cut bacon slices in half.
Fry bacon until partially cooked; drain.
Wrap each shrimp in bacon piece.
Secure with wooden pick.
Set your oven at broil and/or 550°.
Broil 2 to 3 inches from heat until bacon is crisp.

title: jogging in a jug for cholesterol
directions: Mix and take 2 ounces (1/4 cup) a day.
It is thought to lower cholesterol.

title: punch bowl strawberry cake
directions: Break cake mix into small, bite-sized pieces and place in a punch bowl.
Mix sour cream, Cool Whip, powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Pour over cake.
Top with strawberries mixed with glaze.
Refrigerate.

title: baked butter beans
directions: Cut bacon in pieces and fry. Pour off most of fat and fry onions in bacon until soft. Add with rest of ingredients. Bake in serving casserole at 300° for 2 hours.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots slightly; keep crisp.
In a blender, put the remainder of ingredients for marinade.
Slice 1 green pepper and onion and add marinade and sliced carrots.
Will last in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring milk, butter and sugar to a slow boil.
Add rice.
Lower flame to simmer and cook 45 minutes.
Stir often.
Beat together the egg, cream, vanilla and Amaretto (if using) and add to the cooked rice.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in a serving dish and let cool. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Refrigerate.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350 degrees.

title: chicken biscuit bake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl, then transfer into a 13 x 9 greased baking dish. Sprinkle with the cheese; cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Cut biscuits in half and separate. Arrange cut side down over hot chicken mixture. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over biscuits. Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: low-fat macaroni salad
directions: Place cooked macaroni noodles in a large bowl.
Add onions, tomatoes, green peppers, chicken and dressing.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator until good and cold.

title: german hutzet brot
directions: Soak dried fruit in water several hours or overnight.
Prepare yeast in warm water.
Warm the fruit and juice.
Add the shortening, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves to fruit; stir well.
Add yeast and anise and fennel seed; mix well.
Stir in 4 cups flour.
Work in well.
Add 4 more cups flour; work in well. Then add 1 cup flour at a time to make a stiffish batter; careful not to make it too stiff.
Let rise in warm place, covered, to double in size, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: quickie rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast together; add other ingredients and roll out like biscuits.
Cut with large cutter, then fold over and put in pan and let rise.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: peaches in champagne
directions: Peel the peaches.
Halve 3 peaches and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Set aside.
Dice the rest of the peaches. Crack peach pits (vise grips help here).
Take out inner seeds and peel.
Crush the seeds in a mortar.
Add the diced peaches to the seeds and mash together or puree in a blender.
Add 1 cup sugar, mix and force through a sieve.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook sliced carrots 10 minutes and drain.
Grease 8 x 11-inch Pyrex casserole and layer half of the carrots.
Add chopped onions and chopped green pepper.
Add remaining carrots.
Combine soup, margarine and sugar and heat.
Pour soup mixture over carrots. Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until well blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together.
Stir into mixture until moistened.
Add sour milk.
Stir until well blended.
Pour in mashed bananas and mix.
Pour into two greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with Topping.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients, starting with a white sauce made of oleo, flour and milk (cheese added). Pour into large 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Can be divided in 2 casseroles and freeze half.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add next four ingredients.
Mix lightly but not well.
In a separate bowl mix all dry ingredients. Add flour mixture and blend.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan immediately and cool on rack.
Bread may be frozen for later use.
May be served with cream cheese.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Combine eggs and pie mix in large bowl.
Beat all of ingredients together.
Pour into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch) loaf dishes.
Bake in 325° oven for 70 to 80 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in dishes; remove and cool completely before slicing.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Soften butter and add peanut butter.
Add vanilla. Mix.
Mix in sugar.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and canning wax. Dip balls in chocolate.
Makes 100.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Place large piece of foil in bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking pan, or small roaster.
Add butter or margarine on piece of foil.
Place roast on top of butter.
Mix onion soup mix, stewed tomatoes, pepper, and mushrooms and place on top of roast.
Make a sauce with the cornstarch, tomato juice, and A-1 sauce.
Pour over roast, sealing the foil.
Bake at 275° for 3 - 4 hours.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in saucepan. Cook on medium heat about 12 minutes. Stir until thickens. Add coconut and nuts. Mix well until thick. Makes enough for a 2 layer cake.

title: 2 cheese logs
directions: Roll Velveeta between wax paper, approximately 1/4 inch thick. Spread cream cheese on top.
Mix rest of ingredients together. Roll and chill.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place half-cooked noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with thin layer of meat sauce, cheese, filling and then Mozzarella.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fred's favorite dessert
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until light brown.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan or glass dish.

title: baked bananas with rum
directions: Peel bananas; cut in half lengthwise.
Place the bananas in an ovenproof dish.
Combine brown sugar, orange juice, spices and rum.
Heat the mixture and pour over bananas.
Dot with butter. Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until tender.
Baste with juice.
Sprinkle a little more rum on top and serve.
Serves 4.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in order in a cake pan.
Do not mix up cake mix, just sprinkle on in order.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pan.
Mix meal, onion and peppers.
Add eggs and corn.
Mix just a little; add buttermilk and stir well.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable medley casserole
directions: Mix well while still frozen.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until casserole bubbles.
Casserole should be greased 9 x 9-inch size or in case you double the recipe, use a 9 x 13-inch.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt, soda, cinnamon and cloves in a 1-quart mixing bowl.
Rub in shortening with spoon.
Add egg and buttermilk, beating vigorously.
Stir in rolled oats, raisins and nuts.
Blend very well and refrigerate for a few hours.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Cook noodles and brown hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together and heat until cheese melts.

title: chicken chutney
directions: Reserve 3 tablespoons pineapple and mix with onion.
Combine chicken, cashews, pineapple and cucumber.
Combine mayonnaise, chutney and salt.
Now combine all together and chill.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Maintain a very low boil for this time period.
May cook on top of stove or use an electric skillet.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 18 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups.

title: pistachio cake
directions: In a large bowl, place the cake mix, pudding, water, oil and food coloring.
Mix well, then add the eggs and extract; beat at low speed for 5 minutes.
Add pistachio nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then turn onto a wire rack and cool completely.
Frost with your favorite icing. Sprinkle chopped pistachio nuts on top.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown
ground meat (drain).
Saute onions and celery.
Mix it with ground meat and add brown gravy.
Put it into casserole dish. Layer with vegetables and mashed potatoes and Velveeta cheese on top.
Cover the dish and cook at 350° for 1/2 hour.
All ingredients are in layers.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add raisins, wine, fruit and nuts.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Pour into bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Cook in preheated oven at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves about 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients except tomato paste to boil.
Boil for one hour.
Add tomato paste.
Heat to a boil again.
Boil for 5 minutes or until it thickens.
During 5 minutes be sure to stir well.
Makes about 14 quarts.

title: pot roast(crock-pot)
directions: Season beef with garlic powder. In a skillet, brown beef in hot oil. Place potatoes, carrots and onions in a slow cooker. Sprinkle with basil. Top with beef. Pour gravy over all. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high 5 to 6 hours or until a meat thermometer reads 160°. Remove beef and let stand 10 minutes. Slice beef. Serve with vegetables and gravy.

title: hot crackers
directions: Whisk everything together except for the saltines.
Pour over crackers and put in a tight fitting container.
Turn every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Spread out to dry.
Store in a tight container.

title: sam and chan's fantastic fudge
directions: Melt margarine in microwave. Mix sugar, margarine and evaporated milk over high heat until mixture reaches the "soft"-ball stage on a candy thermometer or until a soft ball is formed when dropped in a cup of cool water. Reduce heat to low and add vanilla. Stir in chocolate chips a few at a time. Stir in Marshmallow Creme one spoonful at a time. Pour into a flat container to cool.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Mix water chestnuts, celery, soup and mayonnaise.
Lightly grease 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place big chunks of chicken in dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, dry pudding and well drained fruit. Form into ball and roll into the chopped nuts to cover. Refrigerate to cool.
Serve with cinnamon graham crackers, bagels or whatever you desire or eat alone.

title: deer meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into desired shape.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 1 hour.

title: quick french bread
directions: In large bowl, place warm water.
Add salt and sugar. Sprinkle in dry yeast.
Allow yeast to dissolve.
Stir in flour; mix into dough.
Cover and let rise 25 minutes or more (about double).
Form into 2 loaves.
Place on greased cookie sheet that has been sprayed with vegetable spray and then dusted with cornmeal.
Slash loaves and brush with water.
Let rise 5 minutes or more.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes with a pan of water in oven.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Put pineapple in baking pan.
Mix flour and sugar.
Sprinkle over pineapple.
Top with cheese, then crushed crackers and dot with margarine.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli and rice in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in 1/2 jar Cheez Whiz.
In a fry pan, cook onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Add to broccoli mixture.
Stir in soup and mix well. Top with remaining Cheez Whiz.
Sprinkle bread crumbs or croutons on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Mix sifted cake flour, baking soda and cocoa.
Set aside. Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add sour cream alternately with the cake flour mixture. Add flavoring.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or bake in 1 large and one small square cake pan for 35 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and 1/2 cup granulated sugar.
Add vanilla and egg.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill.

title: crunchy pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash seeds thoroughly and drain.
Spread on cookie sheet. Roast in a 375° oven 20 to 30 minutes to dry.
Increase heat to 400°.
Dot seeds with margarine and brown evenly.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Cool and serve.

title: beef broth
directions: Cover meat with water; bring to a boil, then simmer 3 hours.

title: do-ahead beef dinner casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper, stirring until vegetables are tender.
Pour off drippings; stir in soup, tomato sauce, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into ungreased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate (overnight, if desired).
To bake, place casserole in cold oven. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes in moderate oven (350°).
Spoon potatoes around edge.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and rinse.
Heat milk and cream.
Mix sugar, salt and 3 egg yolks.
Let milk come to a boil.
Add cornstarch, dissolved in a little milk. Add sugar mixture, which a little of the milk mixture has been added.
When thickened, add cooked rice and vanilla.
Beat egg whites stiff. Add 6 tablespoons sugar and a little lemon juice.
Put on top of rice pudding and bake until brown.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Drain liquid from corn and save. Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Add corn, 1/4 cup liquid, milk, butter, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold in crackers and cheese. Spoon into greased 8-cup baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: baked custard
directions: Blessed is the woman who has a smile in her voice, a sparkle in her eyes, a song on her lips, a spring in her step, a warmth in her touch, a depth to her beauty, a purpose to her life, a joy in her faith, a hope in her breast, a love in her heart.

title: vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; add mushroom soup mixture, cheese, pepperoni or bacon and spices.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix all together; put into pie shell.
Place the other pie crust on top.
Press edges down.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sour-sweet sauce
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces; fry until crisp and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients well; add bacon.
Boil gently.
Stir frequently for 20 minutes.
This will become thick after it cools. Store in refrigerator.
Serve with any mixture of green salad.

title: myrt's easy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drop onto greased cookie sheet in balls about the size of a teaspoon.
Press with
a fork.
Bake until done.
Makes about one and a half dozen.

title: microwave diabetic yellow cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch round dish with wax paper.
Pour batter into dish and cover with wax paper.
Elevate dish in oven on glass saucer.
Cook on Low for 6 minutes and then cook on High for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes and peel off wax paper.

title: carrot soup
directions: Bring carrots, chicken broth, dill, sugar, salt and pepper to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Melt 1/4 c. butter.
Add one onion (chopped) and cook for 5 minutes until soft and beginning to turn brown.
Add 1/4 c. flour.
Cook - stirring - 3 minutes.
Stir into carrot mixture. Puree carrot mixture in blender in batches.
Transfer each batch to large bowl then return to Dutch oven.
Stir in 2 c. half and half.
Cook until heated through about 5 minutes.
DO NOT BOIL. Makes 8 cups.
This is one of my most favorite recipes!

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Place in a casserole dish.
Melt butter with cheese.
Pour over carrots.
Crumble crackers over top. Sprinkle with melted butter.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: minestrone
directions: In 8-quart pot over medium heat, saute: onion, carrots, celery, zucchini, potatoes, cabbage and garlic in hot oil and melted butter. Saute 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: barbecued beef sandwich filling
directions: In a large skillet, combine beef, brown sugar, mustard, pepper, water, vinegar and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add salt, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until desired consistency.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: Roll nuts and dates in 1/2 cup flour and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add orange rind.

title: seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add Crab Delights and vegetables; stir over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasonings; cook 1 minute more.
Garnish with chow mein noodles.
Serve immediately or over rice.

title: nana denapoli's easter bread(italian)
directions: It wasn't Easter without Nana DeNapoli's Easter Bread.
She had a special bread for everyone.
It always had a surprise egg in the center.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant into chunks (skin on).
Cook eggplant in water until tender.
Drain.
Add melted margarine, bread crumbs, eggs and seasonings.
Pour into greased casserole.
May sprinkle top with additional bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix lime Jell-O with 2 cups water.
Pour into mold and let set.
Whip rich whip.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth. Fold in crushed pineapple, drained and beaten rich whip.
Pour onto lime Jell-O which has been set.
Refrigerate.
Turn out of mold on platter.
May be put in Xmas tree mold and used for Xmas dinner.

title: chicken fajita salad
directions: In a bowl, combine 4 tablespoons oil, lime juice, parsley, garlic, cumin and oregano. Pour 1/2 into a large resealable plastic bag.
Add the chicken and seal the bag; turn to coat chicken. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Cover and refrigerate remaining marinade. Drain and discard marinade from chicken.

title: don carson's mama's butterscotch pie
directions: Blend the cornstarch, flour and sugar in a heavy saucepan. Beat in the egg yolks.
Slowly beat in the milk and the water. Place over medium heat and cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture boils and is thick (about 2 minutes after it starts to boil).
Beat in the butter and vanilla and pour into a cooled prebaked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: chicken fritters
directions: Beat until fluffy the eggs.
Add sugar, milk and salad oil. Mix ingredients and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Continue mixing until smooth.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix in separate pan.
Spread on top of potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: avocado chiffon pie
directions: In medium saucepan, mix gelatine with 3 tablespoons sugar. Blend in egg yolks beaten with milk.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes. With wire whip, blend in avocado and lemon juice.
Pour into a large bowl and chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.

In a medium bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form, gradually adding remaining sugar (1 tablespoon) and beat until stiff. Fold into gelatine mixture. Turn into prepared crust. Chill until firm. Garnish, if desired, with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: male cookies
directions: x	7
1/2-inch pan.
Pour melted oleo over sugar and mix all together, adding eggs last.
Bake slowly for about 30 to	40
minutes in a 325° oven.
Cool in pan, cut and dust	with powdered
sugar.
Important:
Dust	and grease pan with flour.

title: firecracker chicken
directions: Marinate the chicken breasts in the rest of the ingredients. Marinate for 15 minutes while you preheat broiler or outdoor grill.
Cook over medium heat, 4 to 6-inches, from oven broiler. Broil 3 to 4 minutes per side until juices run clear.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Cook stew beef until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Pour beef drippings in measuring cup.
Add water to drippings to total 4 cups.
Pour the 4 cups of liquid back into the beef.
Add rice, oleo, salt and pepper.
Bring rice and beef to a boil and simmer until water is gone, about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve warm.

title: cheezy cherry torte
directions: Crush pretzels with rolling pin.
Melt butter in medium saucepan and add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add pretzels and mix well.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press balance into 9 x 13-inch pan, ungreased.
Place in freezer while mixing other ingredients.

title: eloise's rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Make a topping by mixing together 1/3 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup nuts and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add to the top of the batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump sliced peaches and crushed pineapple in large cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Top with sliced or melted margarine. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm.
Delicious with ice cream.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Place cut chicken in a single layer in shallow casserole. Brush chicken with 2 tablespoons melted butter -- Sprinkle with salt, pepper & paprika. Bake uncovered 30 minutes. While chicken is baking, melt 3 tablespoons butter in skillet over medium/low heat. Cook sliced mushrooms until tender. Melt 1/4 cup butter in a saucepan over medium heat -- blend in 1/4 cup flour. Remove from heat & gradually add chicken broth and cream. Return to heat stirring constantly until mixture boils. Remove from heat & add sherry, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1/4 teaspoon poultry seasoning. Cook spaghetti according to directions -- drain well. In a large bowl combine spaghetti, mushrooms, chicken & sauce. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese & bake uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and cooking oil; mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with milk in double boiler.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Bake 1/2 of batter for 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven. Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on cake.
Pour caramel mixture on top of this; spread remaining cake batter on top.
Bake 17 to 20 minutes.

title: p.t.a. pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add one egg at a time, mixing well after each. Alternate flour and milk. Blend thoroughly.
Add flavoring. Grease cake pan and dust lightly with flour.
Pour in batter and bake 1 1/2 hours. Time may vary depending on oven.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together except grated cheese.
Add grated cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Spray
a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.
Very tasty!

title: tomato juice
directions: Mix well.
Pour in pans and seal.

title: chop suey
directions: Boil celery with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Fry onions.
Add soup and cook 5 minutes.
Add bean sprouts.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Add soy sauce and margarine.
Add cooked celery.
Add hamburg.
Serve with crunchy Chinese noodles.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy pot, mix all the ingredients except the vanilla. Stir frequently until butter is melted. Boil until a soft ball is formed in glass of ice water. Do not get impatient and remove from stove before this happens. Remove from stove and add the vanilla and mix well. Place the pot in a larger pan of ice cold water and let set until the mixture is cooled. Pour into a buttered baking pan. When hard, cut into squares. Add nuts if you wish.

title: southern chess tart
directions: Divide pastry into 24 equal parts; roll each into circle 3 1/2 to 4 inches in diameter.
(I roll a small ball of pastry and then press it in tart pan.)
Line 24 small tart pans with pastry.
Mix sugar and flour; beat egg, milk, vanilla and butter thoroughly. Fold in nuts.
Place 1 scant tablespoon mixture in each tart.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.

title: double cherry cake
directions: Let Jell-O, boiling water and cool water set at room temperature.
Punch holes 1/2-inch apart and pour liquid over cake.
Refrigerate while making icing.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: Stir-fry celery, onion, salt and ginger in hot oil until tender-crisp (3 to 5 minutes).
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add chicken to hot oil and stir-fry until no longer pink (10 minutes). Return vegetables to pan with chicken.
Drain canned vegetables and add to pan.
Add bouillon cubes and stir until dissolved.
Combine soy sauce and cornstarch until smooth.
Add to chicken and vegetables and cook until sauce boils and thickens.
Serve over hot rice.

title: hearty casserole
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until tender; drain and set aside. Brown ground beef, onion and peppers in skillet; drain fat. Combine with soup.
Stir in noodles, olives and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Place in greased casserole dish and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine corn bread mix, eggs, margarine, broccoli, onion, cheese and salt in bowl. Mix well. Spoon into baking dish sprayed with cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and set.

title: oyster soup
directions: Inspect oysters and remove small bits of shell.
Melt the butter. Add the oysters and their liquid and cook until the edges of the oysters begin to curl. Add milk and salt and heat just to boiling. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion; drain.
In medium bowl, mix soups and enchilada sauce.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch casserole with chips, sauce mixture, meat, beans and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: veggie bar
directions: Make night before.
On cookie sheet, spread out crescent roll on pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; let cool.
Mix salad dressing, cream cheese, cottage cheese and mayo; spread over cooled crescent.
Mix veggies; place on top.
Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.

title: doug's lemon pound cake
directions: Cream oil, butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternate adding dry ingredients and milk.
Add flavorings.
Place in a greased pan.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Put asparagus in a pan with the stock and onion.
Cover the pan; bring to a boil and simmer 6 to 8 minutes or until the asparagus is tender.
Reserve a few tips for garnish.
Work asparagus and liquid through a nylon sieve or puree in a blender. Melt the butter in a large pan; stir in flour and cook, stirring until straw colored.
Take from heat and add the puree.
Season and bring the soup to a boil, stirring and simmer 2 to 3 minutes. Mix the egg yolks and cream together and add a little of the hot soup before adding this mixture to the remaining soup.
Reheat carefully without boiling.
Adjust seasonings; add reserved asparagus tips.

title: apple yam delight
directions: Mix together oats, flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until evenly mixed and crumbly.
In a 6 inch x 10 inch x 2 inch baking dish, arrange a
little less than half the applesauce. Sprinkle with 1/2 tsp. cinnamon.
Spoon 3 Tbsp. topping over the applesauce base.
Evenly arrange the yams.
Spread remaining applesauce over yams.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon.
Add rest of topping and spread evenly.
Bake at 350 degrees about 30 - 40 minutes.
Top with marshmallows or whipped cream, if desired.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, softened cream cheese and taco mix with beaters on medium.
Put mixture in a medium round pizza pan or cookie sheet and spread mixture out to cover bottom of sheet.
Add chopped lettuce, then tomatoes, then cheese, then sliced black olives.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Combine butter and garlic.
Dip chicken in butter, then in crumb mixture. Arrange in single layer in baking pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: crabs and spaghetti
directions: In a large pot, pour in oil. Add garlic.
Cook on medium gas until light brown.
Add crabs. Cover and cook until crabs turn red.
Add crushed tomatoes. Add a can of water for each can of tomatoes. Add tomato paste and a can of water for each can of paste. Add basil. Cook on low gas and stir often. Cook for 2 hours.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Place spaghetti in bowl and cover with crab gravy. Serve crabs on side.

title: okra-and-tomato bake
directions: Coat a 1 3/4 quart casserole with cooking spray.
Layer half of	okra, bacon, tomato and onion slices.
Sprinkle with 1/8 teaspoon
pepper.
Repeat
layers.	Sprinkle
water
over vegetables.
Cover	and
bake
at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yield:
6 (2/3 cup) servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat eggs; mix corn syrup, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°; then lower heat to 350°.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes, until top is brown and crisp or until firm like pecan pie.

title: baked manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Prepare sauce.
Blend tomato sauce, paste and water until well blended. Stir in garlic, oregano, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper. Simmer over low heat for 1/2 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, egg, 1/2 of Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Using teaspoon fill cooled manicotti shells with cheese mixture.
Spread a thin layer of sauce on bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.
Place stuffed shells, side by side in pan.
Cover with remaining spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple glaze for ham
directions: In saucepan, cook ingredients over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens, then boil 1 minute.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: sangria(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Cut outer orange peel into a spiral and place in a container; squeeze the orange and add juice to container. Add juice of 1 lemon; add slices of another lemon. Add wine, sugar and brandy. Stir and chill; finally, add club soda.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and roll into balls.
Melt wax and chocolate bits in double boiler.
Dip each ball.
Use fork to lift out.
Dry on wax paper.

title: old-fashioned banana cake
directions: Grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans.
Sift in large bowl first 4 ingredients.
Mix milk, lemon juice, butter and bananas. Add alternately to dry ingredients.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Frost.

title: ribbon cookies
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder and add to first mixture.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Stir chocolate and nuts into one part; add a few drops of food coloring to another.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Rinse beans.
Soak overnight.
Boil beans slowly until skin bursts.
Drain beans; add pork (or bacon) and onion.
Mix salt, molasses, sugar and mustard with 1 cup boiling water and pour over bean mixture.
Then add approximately 4 cups boiling water (just enough to cover beans).
Cover and bake on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into two well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 250° to 300° from 1 to 2 hours.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows together.
Add pudding and then fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Put in Pyrex oblong dish and chill.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter and bread with milk.
Add pineapple. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great with ham.
May be served hot or cold.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Mix together other ingredients except noodles and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with noodles and bake, uncovered, 15 minutes more.

title: plum cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and 3/4 cup sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, milk and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for
4 minutes.
Grease bottom and sides of an 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Place plums on top, pushing one edge of each half down 1/4-inch into batter.
Dot with butter.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar and cloves; mix well.
Sprinkle over plums.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: walk to school cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add vanilla, flour, salt and nuts to creamed mixture. Drop cookies on sheet pan and flatten with fork. Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 package pistachio pudding, eggs, oil, 7-Up and walnuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato casserole ii
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and place into 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.
Add topping and bake for 10 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and finish up with milk.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and zucchini. Add remaining ingredients, mixing lightly by hand. Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or use baking sheet for 1 hour.

title: fresh turkey breasts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, thyme, rosemary,
tarragon and garlic.
Drizzle 1/2 over turkey in shallow roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to pan and drizzle with remaining butter mixture.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour. Make gravy with the juice.

title: hepburns brownies
directions: First, melt chocolate and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in flour, salt and chopped nuts.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Cook for 40 minutes at 325°.
Cool for a while; cut into squares.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, pudding mix and water; chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into serving dishes; chill.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Combine in punch bowl; add crushed ice and serve.

title: carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook in a little water until tender. Drain.
Add Cheez Whiz and melt.
Add cream of mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Put in a 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: panic
directions: Pour pie filling into a greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 minutes to 1 hour, depending on size. Serve as is or with whipped cream.

title: baked ziti
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package.
Drain.
Meanwhile, cook ground beef, onions and garlic; drain.
Mix cooked beef, pasta, spaghetti sauce and seasonings in a large bowl.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix the flour, margarine and nuts and pat in bottom of an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: fried catfish
directions: Brush fillets lightly with half the mustard. Place cornmeal, salt and pepper in a plastic bag. Drop in catfish one at a time and shake until completely coated. Brush fillets lightly with remaining mustard. Return them to bag and shake again. Fry fillets in deep hot oil (330°) until they float to the top and are golden brown. Drain well.

title: garlic french rolls
directions: Mix yeast in water; add margarine.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add yeast mixture.
Stir chives in last.
Let rise; make into rolls or bread.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in peanut butter, then flour.
Pour into a greased 10 x 5-inch loaf pan or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated oven about 1 1/2 hours for large pan and 50 to 60 minutes for the small ones. After 15 minutes of cooking, sprinkle finely chopped peanuts on top to give it a crunchy topping.

title: lye soap
directions: Dissolve lye in water.
Heat grease to 120° or until all is melted.
When you mix the water and lye, it will become very hot. Allow to cool to about 80° before mixing.
Slowly pour the melted lard into the lye mixture, stirring slowly until the mixture becomes thick like honey.
Pour into a plastic pan, cover with a cloth, let set until cool and cut in squares.
I mix my soap in a plastic bucket.
If you have old grease (bacon), melt and strain before making soap with it.

title: down to earth granola
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix oats, almonds, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon.
In a saucepan, warm the oil and honey. Whisk or stir in vanilla when warm.
Carefully pour liquid over oat mixture.
Stir gently with a wooden spoon; finish mixing by hand.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture on bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips. Mix well.
Bake in preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Then add cream, butter and vanilla.
Mix and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until it thickens.
Then pour over cake or ice cream.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix rolled oats, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Add the margarine and a mixture of egg and extract; mix thoroughly.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In deep frying pan add small amount of olive oil.
Add chicken pieces to hot oil.
Brown slightly.
Add soy sauce and vegetables. Reduce heat, cover and stir often.
Takes approximately 25 to 30 minutes to simmer.
Serve with white or yellow rice.
Also works well with beef or pork.

title: dingbats(date balls)
directions: Cook oleo, sugar, chopped dates, chopped nuts and eggs for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Add vanilla. Pour over Rice Krispies and mix well. When easy to handle, form into small balls and roll in flaked coconut and chopped nuts.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, in saucepan.
Heat until mixture is melted and thoroughly blended.
Pour into fondue pot. Cut up French bread and dip.

title: jello cake
directions: Chill jello until slightly jelled.
Add half of Cool Whip and all of pineapple.
Crumble half of cake in bottom of pan.
Add jello mixture.
Take other half of cake and crumble on top of mixture.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Add coconut.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add flakes, oatmeal, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Place by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and press flat with fork which has been dipped in water.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add beaten eggs, milk, butter and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Blend in cocoa and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients alternately with water, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in kraut until all mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Peel and slice carrots; cook in salted water until just tender (do
not
overcook).
Drain
carrots.
Mix
all
other ingredients
and bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly. Pour
over	the carrots and stir well.
Cover and refrigerate. Will keep six weeks.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix these ingredients together and set aside.
Prepare about 5 pounds venison by trimming all fat and waste away.
Slice the meat with the grain in slices 1/4-inch thick and 1-inch wide at most. (If meat is semi-frozen, it will be easier to work with.)
Layer meat in a large, flat, glass dish, covering each layer with marinade before starting the next.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in the refrigerator overnight.

title: almond caramel apples
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, butter and cream.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Boil over moderate heat to very firm ball stage (250°), stirring occasionally to prevent scorching. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Insert skewer into each apple and dip into syrup.
Roll in chopped almonds (roasted). Makes 8 to 12 apples, depending on size.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil; add broccoli.
Mix soup, milk, water, rice and cheese spread in saucepan; heat to boiling. Arrange broccoli mixture in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Form sausage into small balls and brown in a large skillet. Drain well.
Put sausages in chafing dish and spoon apple butter over sausage.
Keep warm and serve with toothpicks.
These are simple to make and everyone loves them.

title: party treats
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Spread on cocktail rye bread.
Place this slice of cucumber on top.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter flavor Crisco.
Beat eggs in a large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer until light and foamy.
Add brown sugar, butter flavor Crisco and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.

title: lobster salad(recipe for 2)
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients.
Add 3 ounces of Tarragon Dressing and arrange on a 7-inch plate.
Garnish with a leaf of romaine and reddichio lettuce and a spring of tarragon.
Put a few of the medallions on the top of the salad.

title: oven porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix together; roll into balls.
Place in pan.
Mix water and tomato sauce.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, then uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Cut cabbage, onion and pepper into bowl. Sprinkle sugar over. Don't stir! Bring rest of ingredients to a boil. Pour over vegetables. Don't stir! Let cool and refrigerate. Will keep for 6 weeks.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain grease.
Add pepper, onion, mushrooms and spices.
Cook a couple of minutes before adding Prego sauce.
After adding sauce, let simmer approximately 20 minutes.
Cook noodles to desired tenderness.
Add twisters about 3 minutes before egg noodles.
In a large casserole dish, layer noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: peanut rocky road
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Fold in peanuts and marshmallows.
Spoon in mounds on wax paper.
Chill until firm.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook in iron skillet on stove, then in oven at 325° for 2 hours.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Mix together soup, milk and sour cream with thawed hash browns. Put into 9 x 13-inch pan; put pork chops on top.
Cover with cheese and onion rings.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and put more cheese and onion rings on top.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix soup, salt, pepper, vinegar, oil, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Place carrots (drained), bell pepper and onion in large bowl.
Pour mixture over carrots.
Cover and seal. Place in refrigerator.
Serve chilled.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Combine drained pasta and vegetables with remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Makes 8 side dish servings.

title: ambrosia
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients gently.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: teatime lassies (pecan tarts)
directions: Mix thoroughly with a fork, form into 24 equal balls and press into small muffin pans.

title: oatmeal crisp cookie
directions: Sift dry ingredients; put aside.
Cream margarine; add sugars, eggs, juice and vanilla and mix well.
Add oatmeal, coconut, rind and nuts; mix and blend well.
Then add the dry ingredients. Blend well and form 4 logs.
Roll in wax paper and freeze for a couple of hours.
Remove from freezer one at a time and slice thin on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
It makes a lot of cookies.

title: arthur's salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice and pudding.
Cook over medium heat until clear and thick.
Cool.
Mix fruits.
Pour pudding mixture over fruit and mix well.
Chill.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Shape meatballs and brown.
Heat ketchup, jelly and a dash of Tabasco.
Add drained meatballs to sauce.
Keep warm while serving.

title: bride's easy chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking pan in single layer.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°, covered loosely.

title: spanish hot dogs
directions: Saute sliced onion until soft.
Add tomatoes and cook 15 minutes.
Add sliced hot dogs and cook 10 minutes more.
Boil rice until tender.
Excellent buffet meal.
Serve in 2 separate bowls. Guests take a serving of rice and pour tomato-hot dog mixture over it.

title: diet strawberry pie
directions: Let pudding cool at least 5 minutes.
Add strawberry Jell-O. Beat well until smooth.
Then stir in 4 cups sliced strawberries. Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: rotel potato casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Add cheese and melt. Add tomatoes and mushrooms. Pour this mixture over potatoes in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut small portion off tops of peppers.
Drop in boiling water; cook for 5 minutes.
Discard stems and seeds.
Take leftover parts of tops and dice.
Cook in hot oil with diced onion.
Cook until softened.
Add ground meat and cook until browned.
Cook rice according to directions.
Add to meat mixture.
Add spices and tomatoes plus tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Place well drained peppers in baking dish.
Stuff with tomato and meat mixture.
Place extra over and around peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tiny apple cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place paper liners in 16 (1/3 cup) muffin cups.
Place a cookie in the bottom of each and set aside. In a small skillet, melt butter.
Add apples, cook and stir until tender, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; spoon over apples.
With an electric mixer, beat cream cheese, eggs, sour cream, vanilla and remaining sugar until smooth. Spoon over apples.
Bake until set, 25 to 28 minutes.
Cool on a rack; remove cakes.
Cover and refrigerate until cold.
Garnish with sour cream, apple slices and crushed vanilla wafers, if desired.
Yield:

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Crumble crackers, melt butter and mix.
Place cut up chicken in large baking dish.
Mix soups and broth together with sour cream, pour over chicken.
Put cracker crumbs on top of mixture.

title: blender custard
directions: Mix all together in blender for 3 minutes.
Pour in pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
May use coconut instead of nutmeg.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Saute beef, zucchini, onion and seasonings in lightly greased skillet until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are crisp and tender.
Stir frequently.
Add green chilies, rice, sour cream and one cup of cheese.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Salt and pepper.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli; mix all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered baking dish at 325° for 1 hour.

title: eight layer spread
directions: Stir together beans and picante or taco sauce. Arrange lettuce on a 12 inch platter, leaving a 2 inch open rim at edge of platter. Spread bean mixture over lettuce making a layer about 1/4 inch thick. Then layer sour cream. top with cheese, onion, and olives. Cover and chill up to 24 hours. Before serving, arrange tomatoes on top. Arrange the chips on a platter around the spread. Yields 16 servings.

title: chicken with carrots and tarragon
directions: Melt margarine in a 4-quart saucepan.
Add onion and garlic. Saute for 1 minute.
Add chicken, carrots, parsley, tarragon and pepper.
Cook until chicken is lightly browned.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water.
Let stand.
Mix all ingredients.
Place portion in center of each cabbage leaf.
Fold sides of leaf over meat.

Roll up and secure with toothpick. Brown in large skillet or Dutch oven with 2 tablespoons of oil. Add 1 large can tomato sauce and 1 large can of tomato paste, 2 cans of water, 3 tablespoons brown sugar, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Mix this together before adding to cabbage rolls.
Cook on low heat for about 2 hours; if necessary, add more water during cooking.

title: salmon and noodle casserole
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour.
Gradually add milk; cook and stir until mixture is thick and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain salmon; sprinkle with lemon juice.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of noodles, salmon, parsley and onion and white sauce.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake about 25 minutes at 375° or until bubbly hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and milk to a boil over medium heat. Boil 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add nuts if desired. Pour into greased cookie sheet and let sit overnight.
When cool cut into pieces.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Use low-fat dressing and no salt for healthy salad.
Stays fresh for several days.

title: peach dessert
directions: Break cake in bite-size pieces and spread in a dish.
Dissolve gelatin using only 2 cups boiling water; pour over cake.
Add sliced peaches.
Let congeal in refrigerator.
Prepare instant pudding according to package.
Spread over gelatin and cake. Spread whipped topping over all.

title: beans
directions: Soak beans in cold water for 8 hours or overnight.
Do not drain.
Add enough fresh water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Add onion.
Simmer slowly in a covered pot, preferably earthenware. When skins begin to wrinkle, add bacon drippings.
As liquid is absorbed, add more water, always hot.
Cook about 3 1/2 hours. Add salt and cook another 30 minutes or until beans are soft. Separate beans from broth by adding beans to frying pan, a little at a time, with additional bacon drippings.
Mash beans with spoon and add broth, a little at a time.
When all beans have been mashed, saute the whole mixture until it thickens into a heavy paste that can be rolled up.
(Do not let it get too dry.)
Serve hot with chopped onion and grated cheese on top.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: jellied applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Let cool. Refrigerate until consistency of egg whites.
Add fruits and celery.
Stir well. Pour into pan or molds and refrigerate until set.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Soak raisins in water until soft, then drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugars, flour and butter.
Mix well.
Add chips and nuts.
Pour in crust.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: elegant eggplant entree
directions: Thirty to forty-five minutes before starting, peel eggplants and cut in lengths.
Place in colander and salt; let cry so bitterness may leave eggplant.
Rinse in cold water.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil; do not chop garlic.
Add tomatoes and water.
Cook down until it becomes a sauce.
Add into the sauce the eggplants and cook for about 40 minutes.
Cook this recipe in a shallow, large pan, not a deep pan.
Cook pasta; drain.
Place on dish; add eggplant mixture and cheese.
Delicious!
Enjoy!

title: broiled or barbecued chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken halves.
Be sure chicken is dry, place skin side down on broiler pan, brush top lightly with basting mixture.
Place 6 to 8-inches under broiler.
Broil for approximately 10 minutes, turn, brush skin side with mixture, broil another 10 minutes.
Do this twice or until chicken is cooked thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, beat eggs and mix in the mayonnaise. Cook broccoli as directed on the package.
Drain well and mix into the egg mixture.
Add cheese, 1/2 can of onions and pepper.
Bake at 350° until set for about 30 minutes.
Top with the remaining onions during the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange half the slices on bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
In large mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand, water and extract.
Mix well.
Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour half the cream mixture over cake slices.
Arrange peach slices on top.
Repeat layering of cake slices and cream mixture.
Chill for 4 hours or until set.
Cut into squares to serve.
Refrigerate leftovers. Easy to make and hard to resist.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in a small amount of boiling salted water, about 8 minutes. Drain. Combine celery, soup and pimiento; spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and almonds over celery mixture.
Drizzle margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel clusters
directions: Heat margarine in heavy 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat until melted.
Stir in sugar.

Stir frequently with wood spoon 4 to 5 minutes while mixture melts and begins to turn golden brown. Continue cooking 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture is golden and no longer granular.
Remove from heat. Quickly add cereal and mix until cereal is completely coated. Spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into bite-size pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: For German chocolate cake, bake cake mix.
Between thin layers and on top, spread with Cool Whip and sliced bananas. Refrigerate.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots. Drain and set aside.
Saute onion in butter. Slice Velveeta cheese and melt into butter.
Mix cheese sauce and carrots.
Place in casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except hash browns.
Add this mixture to hash browns.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll dough out on lightly floured surface to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with floured donut cutter.
Fry in oil (375°) about 1 1/2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Cool slightly and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: cream cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and almond extract.
In a separate bowl, combine margarine and vanilla.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Roll or press each into a 3-inch circle.
Dip each cream cheese cube into margarine, then in sugar mixture.
Place each cube into center of each circle biscuit.
Fold dough over cube (cover completely).
Shape into balls.
Dip each ball into margarine, then roll in sugar mixture. Place seam side down in ungreased muffin cup.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 18 minutes or until brown.
Store in refrigerator.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Put meat mixture in a casserole.
Add beans and soup, then mix.
Top with Tater Tots and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, shortening and brown sugar together.
Keep out 1/2 cup crumbs.
Mix rest of ingredients into remaining crumbs.
Place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put 1/2 cup of crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil until hot.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add crushed tomatoes, salt, Italian seasoning and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add wine.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Serve over freshly cooked pasta.
Yield: About 4 cups.

title: butternut snow balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Mix together.
Then add nuts. When cool, roll in powdered sugar twice. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: For cornbread, combine first 6 ingredients in order listed; mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until done.

title: three vegetable casserole
directions: Cook peas and limas according to package directions; do not drain.
Combine peas, limas and remaining ingredients except butter and stuffing mix.
Stir to combine.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Mix together the flour, soda, salt and spices; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth; stir in oatmeal.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large skillet, cook sausage until brown. Separate crescent rolls into triangles. Place in ungreased 12-inch rimmed pizza pan with points toward the center. Press together, seal perforations and form a circle. Turn edges to make rim. Sprinkle sausage over crust. Top with hash browns. Add peppers and onions if desired. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Stir egg, milk, salt and pepper in a small bowl. Pour over pizza evenly. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 20 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a 3-quart soup pot, saute sausage until lightly browned; drain all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onion, peppers and garlic and cook until tender.
Add corn and chicken stock.
Bring to a boil. Add half and half.
Heat, add cornstarch (3 tablespoons mixed with 3 tablespoons of water).
Heat well, will not be very thick. Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Put apples in a large bowl.
Break eggs over apples and stir. Add rest of ingredients,
one at a time, stirring after each addition.
Bake in
x
13-inch baking pan in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion, salt and pepper and butter until tender; drain.
Melt margarine and mix with 1/2 of dressing and other ingredients.
Mix the other 1/2 of the dressing with 1 stick margarine and mix separately.
Spoon squash mixture into greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining dressing and margarine mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes whole, then cool, peel and dice them.
Mix with the rest of ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water. Add remaining ingredients. Stir and freeze. Add 1 (2-liter) of 7-Up. Remove from freezer 1 hour prior to serving. Pour 7-Up over frozen punch. Serve slushy.

title: white chili
directions: Simmer about 30 minutes. Stir often to keep from sticking. Add a little water if too thick.

title: chicken sauce piquant
directions: Chop up chicken into cubes. Brown sausage and chicken; add Tony's seasoning. Using a blender, blend celery, onion, bell pepper, and small amount of water. Saute for 10 minutes; add other ingredients and more water. Cook for 1 1/2 hours. Gravy will be thin. Serve over rice.

title: pork chop-fried rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, bring the 1 3/4 cups water to boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in rice.
Cover and set aside.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and crumble, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings; set aside.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Measure flour into small saucepan.
Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thick.
Cool.
Blend butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and vanilla and beat until light and of spreading consistency.
Frost cake and refrigerate.
Very like whipped cream.
Very good!

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Cream cheese should be room temperature.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into any kind of pie shell.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip and enjoy.

title: easy swedish meatballs
directions: Combine bread crumbs, seasonings, eggs and milk.
Add ground beef, mixing lightly.
Shape into small meatballs.
Roll in flour, coating generously.
Using a large heavy skillet, brown meatballs in oil for about 10 minutes, turning to brown all sides.
Remove meatballs from pan.
Blend flour into pan drippings; gradually stir in broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Add meatballs and simmer 10 minutes.
Makes about 60 meatballs.

title: chicken wings
directions: Chop garlic.
Add soy sauce and all remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Add chicken wings and marinate in refrigerator overnight or all afternoon, making sure liquid mixture covers all chicken from time to time.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Pout puittig in crust.
Mix egg yolks and sugge.
Pout the meringue in the crust.
And bake on 350°.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order given.
Mix well.
Roll in small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and slightly flatten each cookie.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Spray loaf pan with no stick cooking spray.
Mold mixture into loaf shape in pan. Bake for 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: rogalach(crescent cookies from grams)
directions: Mix the butter, cheese and salt in mixer until creamy.
Mix in flour and blend thoroughly.
Make 14 balls from this mix.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
Make the filling of the nuts, sugar and cinnamon and add the beaten white of an egg.
The next day, roll each ball into a 6-inch circle.
Cut each circle into 6 pie shaped wedges.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of filling on each section and roll, beginning at the wide end.
Form into crescents and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned, about 7 or 8 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick of butter together and set aside. Cream other stick of butter with sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, then add Milky Way mixture and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Mix vinegar, water and all seasonings together.
Pour over vegetables.
Colorful and tasty salad.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter 5 minutes.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour in greased casserole.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars.
Then add eggs, vanilla and water.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, soda, chocolate chips and nuts (if desired).
Drop by tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 360° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack before storing.
Makes about 12 dozen cookies.
One slice of bread in top of container keeps cookies soft.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain. Mix beans with meat. Spray casserole with Pam. Layer, starting with a layer of corn tortillas and next a layer of meat/bean mixture. Keep alternating tortillas and meat. Mix chicken soup and Ro-Tel. Pour over casserole and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: italian medley
directions: Boil spareribs 30 minutes; drain.
Place ribs, fryer and sausage in a large Dutch oven pan.
Cover with 1 large sliced onion and 2 crushed cloves garlic and cover with sauce.

title: my daughter's perfect pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening with fork until finely made pieces. Add other ingredients; mix until combined.
(May need a bit more water.)
Form a large ball and divide into 4 or 5 pieces.
Form into balls and flatten slightly.
Wrap each in Saran Wrap.
Keeps very well frozen for 3 months.
Makes 5 pie crusts.

title: fruit tart dessert
directions: Spread pie filling evenly in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, then spread cake mix (right out of package).
Melt oleo and drizzle oleo over cake mix.
Put in oven for about 1 hour at 350° to 375°. Let cool; serve with whipped cream.

title: lime ribbon delight
directions: Bake cake mix (per box instructions) in 9-inch layer pans. Cool.
Pour boiling water over gelatin in bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in fruit juice; chill until thickened but not set.
Stir in pineapple, nuts and lemon juice.
Place 2 strips of aluminum foil in each of the pans.
Place the cake in the pans.
Put gelatin mixture on the cake layers.
Chill until firm.
In a bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar until stiff. With foil strips, lift cake out and stack.
Frost sides with whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift flour and sugar in bowl.
Blend in butter.
Pat evenly in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Meanwhile, beat together eggs, sugar, baking powder, lemon juice and salt.
Pour over baked crust and return to oven 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut in squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: baked pears with marshmallows
directions: Place drained pears in a baking dish with 1/3 cup of their juice.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over pears. Place a paper-thin slice of lemon on each pear half and a marshmallow on top of the lemon slice.
Place in a moderately hot oven (400°).

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil well. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add apples. Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together and add to apple mixture. Add chopped nuts. Bake in ungreased tube pan or greased Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick is clean. Let set 10 minutes; turn on plate. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Mix rice with soup.

Swish some water around in the cans. Spread this mixture in bottom of casserole or large baking dish. Cover with pieces of chicken; sprinkle contents of package of onion soup over the chicken and rice (I used a roaster).
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 2 hours.
Just forget about it in the oven.
You'll know when it is done; it smells delicious.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat.
Add part of banana pulp.
Beat and add part of flour (with soda, baking powder and salt added).
Next add bananas and flour until all is mixed.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased bread pan or angel food pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
When bread leaves side of pan, it is done.
Use no liquids as banana pulp is the liquid.

title: sea leg dip
directions: Cream dressing, ketchup and cheese until soft.
Mix in onions. When creamy, add in sea legs and chill.

title: chicken n' rice, new style
directions: Cook chicken on top of the stove with the onion soup mix until chicken is tender; debone and skin.
Degrease the broth by placing pot in refrigerator until the grease comes to the top.
Skim the fat off.
Heat the mixture again and bring to a boil.
Add rice and chicken.
Simmer until done.

title: 24 hour omelet
directions: *Sometimes less cheese can be used and add browned sausage or ham (place on top of bread).

title: charleston shrimp and grits
directions: Note:
This classic recipe has many variations. Serve with vine-ripened tomatoes, crisp bacon, toast and preserves for truly wonderful meal.
