title: cousin fern's end of the garden relish
directions: Cook string beans and lima beans in salt water until tender. Drain and add other mixture.
Cook all 20 minutes.
Cool in airtight jars.
(I pour into hot, sterilized jars and process in boiling water for 20 minutes.)

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in glass casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, hot water and sugar.
Put cranberries, orange and apple in food chopper.
Add to Jell-O mixture; add chopped celery and drained pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Chill.

title: bob's coffee dessert
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in coffee.
When cool, add whipped cream.
Pour in glasses.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: seven cup cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar, margarine, egg, oil and vanilla. Mix well. Gradually add the dry ingredients. Mix well. Chill dough for 1 hour or overnight.
Shape dough into small balls. Place on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes.

title: chicken divan crepes
directions: Over medium heat, melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbly.
Add broth and Worcestershire sauce; cook, stirring until thickened.
Add 2 cups cheese; empty sour cream into medium bowl.
Gradually add hot cheese, stirring constantly.
In large shallow baking dish, place cooked broccoli and cooked chicken on each crepe.
Spoon 1 tablespoon sauce over each.
Fold crepes over.
Pour remaining sauce over all.
Sprinkle with remaining cup of cheese.
Cover and heat at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored. Add peel and juice; beat until thick. Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar and the salt. Carefully fold in flour. Beat egg whites until foamy. Add cream of tartar; beat to soft peaks. Gradually add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, beating to stiff peaks. Thoroughly fold whites into yolk mixture. Bake in ungreased 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 55 minutes or until done. Invert pan and cool. Slice cake and serve with 2 tablespoons of Orange Angel Fluff topping (recipe follows).

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Cook rhubarb with sugar and crushed pineapple until done.
Add Sure-Jell and Jell-O.
Fill jelly jars and seal well.

title: old fashioned vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine 1 cup milk and the cornstarch; beat until smooth.
Add 3 cups milk and the sugar.
Cook in double boiler, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.
Beat until light the eggs. Gradually add eggs to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes longer; stir constantly.
Pour through strainer.
Stir in 2 cups milk, the whipping cream, salt and vanilla.
Pour into freezer.
Add more milk, if needed.

title: brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup oil.
Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; blend completely.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
May add chopped pecans.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Salt beef, then roll in flour.
Brown beef in a skillet.
Dip out into baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup with 1 can of water and pour over browned beef.
Bake for 45 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: no name casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Chop tomatoes into small pieces. combine with chopped onion and ground beef.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients except cheese in 2-quart baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute butter and onion.
Put rice in 2-quart saucepan.
Mix soup and milk together and pour 1/2 of it over the rice.
Then add the broccoli and onion.
Put the other 1/2 of soup over that.
Add the cheese over the top.
Bake 1/2 hour or more.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick and easy dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filing into long flat baking dish.
Dump pineapple, juice and all.
Dump dry cake mix lightly over fruits. Do not mix.
Melt margarine and spread evenly over top. (Optional:
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.)
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until top is golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
This is a dessert, not a cake.

title: three bean hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, oil and carrots.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to other mix.
Bake in 3 layers for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dietetic cheesecake
directions: Use blender and combine lemon juice, yolks and gelatin on low. Pour in milk and sugar; blend for one minute on high.
Add cheese by spoonful, blending until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker shell and refrigerate.
Use fresh fruit on top to decorate.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in bowl.
Shape after all seasonings are applied.
Place in loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour about 1/2 small can of tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: potato cheese soup(makes 4 servings)
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Add onion; saute until tender (5 minutes).
Add flour; stir until it starts to turn brown (2 to 3 minutes).
Stir in broth, then milk, stirring constantly. Add potatoes and green onions; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cheese; stir to melt.
Serve topped with cooked, crumbled bacon, if desired.

title: nutritious breakfast drink
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender and drink immediately. Serves 1.

title: monster peanut butter chocolate chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350° with oven rack in center.
For each cookie, cover cookie sheets with foil and grease lightly.
Using an 8-inch pot lid or round baking pan as a pattern, make a ring on the greased surface.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add rice and mushrooms.
Saute until lightly browned.
Stir in soup mix and water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables using coarse blade.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour this over the vegetables.
Heat to boiling and simmer for 3 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: stuffed quahogs(serves 4)
directions: Open quahogs, save shells (wash), chop quahog meat and mix with Ritz crackers, bread crumbs, celery, onion, Louisiana hot sauce and garlic.
Add quahog juice until moist.
Fill quahog half shells with stuffing mix; sprinkle with paprika and bake on cookie sheet for about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add evaporated milk, water and melted butter.
Stir thoroughly.
Mix in cranberries. Spoon into buttered 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack before removing from pan.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix melted butter, flour and sugar. Add water, milk and egg yolks. Cook until thick and top with egg whites.

title: country breakfast
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble, then drain.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in pie shell.
Beat eggs lightly and combine remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Yum! Yum!

title: blender cheese cake
directions: Place eggs, milk, cream cheese, vanilla, sugar and cornstarch in blender container; blend 5 minutes.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Evenly spoon pineapple on batter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Chill before serving (preferably overnight).

title: gala tomato punch
directions: For each egg, use 1 to 2 teaspoons of Pace medium picante sauce and 1 tablespoon of milk.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in picante sauce and milk.
Cook over low heat in a greased nonstick pan, stirring from edges, until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: middle eastern lamb balls
directions: Combine lamb, rice, onion, mint, salt, allspice and pepper and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 12 balls.
Heat oil in skillet, add lamb balls and cook until brown and desired doneness.

title: muh's butter rolls
directions: Put 6 biscuits on floured board and roll two ways.
Do same to other six.
After rolled out, put butter on top of dough; sprinkle nutmeg, cinnamon and sugar on flat roll.
Begin rolling until you have a long roll.
Slice; arrange in a greased pan; do not crowd. Put a little butter on each roll.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture on rolls.
Pour water about 1/2 way up.
Cook at 375° until brown.

title: "yummy" graham dream bars
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Line pan in bottom with whole graham crackers.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt margarine and add other ingredients. Stir until creamy smooth. Pour mixture into greased pan. Nuts may be added if desired.

title: deviled chicken wings
directions: Prepare and clean wings. In food processor, finely grind bread. Measure out 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs. Grind mustard seeds to fine.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix in 9 x 12-inch baking dish and sprinkle with topping.

title: katie's black bean soup
directions: Soak beans in sufficient water to cover by 2 to 3-inches overnight.
Drain beans and save water.
Saute soaked beans in oil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add water from soak and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 3 to 4 hours, until tender and broth is thickened and dark.
Add onion, garlic and herbs during first hour of cooking.
Serve with lemon, sour cream and dark bread.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Wrap water chestnuts with 1/2 slice bacon; secure with toothpicks.
Mix sugar and ketchup; pour over water chestnuts. Broil bacon and water chestnuts, then pour sauce over and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: tasty meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form a loaf.
Place in shallow baking pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: easy beef goulash
directions: Brown beef in oil in heavy saucepan.
Stir in onion soup mix, tomato paste and water.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Serve over hot noodles with dollop of sour cream. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 10 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix next 5 ingredients and spread over the crust.
Mix the vegetables together and firmly press into cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Measure 1/2 cup gelatin and blend into whipped topping.
Tint with small amount of food coloring.
Chill until stiff enough to mound.
Spread over bottom and sides of crust. Spread strawberry halves on top of topping.
Gently spoon remainder of gelatin on top.
Decorate with a few strawberry halves. Chill until gelatin is firm.

title: carrot cake #1
directions: Sift flour with soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Beat eggs until very light, then gradually beat in sugar until mixture is fluffy.
Slowly add oil, beating to keep the mixture light.
Fold in the flour mixture with a spatula, then add carrots, vanilla, grated peel and nuts.
Spread in a greased and floured tube pan, two 9-inch round cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, until cake tests done. Cool in pan(s) for 10 minutes before removing from pan to cool completely.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Cut 4 to 5 slices of bread into cubes to measure 3 cups.
In ovenproof skillet, melt butter; stir in garlic powder.
Add bread cubes.
Toss to coat.
Place in a very slow oven at 225° for about 2 hours.
Refrigerate in a tightly covered container until needed.

title: cloud biscuits(with heavenly taste)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, beaten egg and milk.
Mix well; turn out on floured board and knead several times.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Place on greased pan and bake at 450°
until brown.

title: gary's texas zucchini
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix ingredients and pour into greased dish.
Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese. Add milk, powdered sugar and peanut butter. Mix well and add Cool Whip. Mix well and pour into baked crust. Chill. May top with Cool Whip.

title: fritorta
directions: Cook rice in the broth and water.
When cooked, place in a large bowl and add melted butter.
Mix well and add the cottage cheese, salami, soup mix, salt and pepper.
Beat 9 eggs; stir in mixture.
Add the drained spinach and mix well.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and freeze overnight or refrigerate.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add strawberries and let gel.
Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Mix medium container Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Pour over crust.
Top with firm jello and chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs; mix in sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients and add to moist batter.
Mix in applesauce, nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour five (1-pound) coffee cans.
Fill with batter over 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brisket
directions: Cut most of the fat from brisket.
Rub in tenderizer and Creole seasoning, then roll and tie.
Place on upper rack of Cajun cooker.
Place 4 pork chops on upper end of brisket.
After coals are burning good, place Cajun cooker over coals and place water in pan.
Allow to cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours, depending upon heat and size of brisket.
Cut and serve.

title: bul-gogi(barbecued beef)
directions: Put chopped green onion, soybean sauce, sugar, sesame oil and black pepper in a big pot and mix them together well.
Add wine. Place sliced beef (not too thin) in the sauce mix and have it soaked (at least one good hour).
Take slices out one by one and put them on the grill and you're set.

title: chocolate spider cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in large saucepan. Remove from heat and add chow mein noodles and peanuts if desired. Drop onto wax paper and let cool.

title: date dainties
directions: Bake in two 8-inch greased and floured pans for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pizza balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Form into balls, covering a cube of cheese in the center of each ball.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet.
Cover with pizza sauce and simmer until done. Top with grated cheese.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Put all ingredients in a double boiler over water and stir together.
When warm or sugar dissolves, start to beat with an electric mixer.
Beat until it forms a peak.
Ice cake.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 of chipped beef.
From into a ball and cover with remaining beef.
Serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Blend together until smooth.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well and set aside.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Pour into a greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in pan.
Spread pie filling in pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix together cake mix, nuts and 1 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs and pour melted butter over mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 300° until it bubbles.
Use shallow baking dish or casserole.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil until oil is dissolved.
Sift dry ingredients; add to oil mixture and beat 2 minutes.
Add pumpkin and nuts.
Mix well.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: tea cake
directions: First, with the blender on medium speed, mix eggs and sugar thoroughly until the mixture becomes white.
Add all other ingredients in the same bowl and mix together.
Grease your cake mold or Bundt pan and dust it with some flour.
Pour the mixture in it.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: grandmother's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick banana pie
directions: Layer bananas and vanilla wafers in large dish.
Combine pudding mix and 2 cups milk.
Mix well.
Mix pudding, Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Stir until blended.
Pour over bananas and vanilla wafers.
Chill.

title: cheesy mexican chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in water until done; debone chicken and save water.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and simmer.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth until done. Pour almost all water off.
Add chicken.
Add cheese to sauteed mixture.
Stir until melted.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mushrooms.
Stuff each mushroom with cheese mixture and place four mushroom on each of six squares of foil.
Fold into a packet; seal.
Grill for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tomato soup rolls
directions: Dilute tomato soup with enough water to make 1 pint and heat until warm.
Add sugar and yeast, let stand until bubbling, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add butter, stir and add salt and flour.
Mix and let rise in warm place until light.
Form into desired shape and put in greased muffin tins and allow to rise until double in bulk. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in hot oven.

title: lefse
directions: Peel, boil and rice ten pounds of potatoes.

title: mammaw's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
Real good punch.

title: sauerkraut and pork chops
directions: Put kraut into baking dish.
Put chops on top.
Mix soup, water and brown sugar.
Pour over chops.
Bake at 350° until chops are done. You may have to reduce heat.

title: blue cornmeal muffins
directions: Stir together cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and cumin; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, oil and peppers.
Add egg mixture all at one time to cornmeal mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Grease muffin pans or line with paper baking cups; fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan. Serve warm with cream cheese.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pasta with shrimp and sun-dried tomatoes(4 servings)
directions: In a medium skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the oil and the hot pepper over moderate heat.
Season the shrimp with the salt and add to the skillet.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until the shrimp just turns pink, about 2 minutes.
Add the shallots, sun-dried tomatoes and oregano and cook, stirring occasionally, until the shallots are soft and the shrimp cooked through, about 2 minutes more.
Scrape the contents of the skillet into a large bowl.
Add the arugula, the remaining 1/4 cup olive oil and the lemon juice to the shrimp mixture; toss to combine.
Season with salt to taste.

title: eagle brand milk substitute
directions: Mix.
Then put in the blender.
Will be thin, but will thicken.

title: meat loaf 2
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ketchup.
Press into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain off excess fat.
Spread ketchup on top.
Continue to bake 30 minutes more or until done.

title: wild rice and chicken
directions: Wash rice well.
Cover with water and cook with lid on for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix soup, milk and parsley flakes.
Combine with rice and mix well.
Pour into large, flat casserole.
Place cut up chicken on top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Remove foil for last 30 minutes to brown.

title: skillet stir-fry
directions: Saute seafood in one tablespoon margarine and 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Pam may be used instead.
Heat vegetables in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes until soft.
Combine seafood, vegetables and soy sauce in skillet and mix well.
Serve over white rice.

title: chocolate-date cake
directions: Cover dates with boiling water.
Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add dates and chocolate bits.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and sprinkle with xxxx sugar.

title: carrots vichy
directions: In a wide frying pan, lay carrots flat and add water to cover. Bring to a boil over high heat and then reduce heat to simmer and cover.
Cook until carrots are tender when pierced, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.

title: milky way homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in freezer.
Add enough homogenized milk to finish filling freezer.
If using electric freezer, leave in freezer until freezer stops running.

title: pork chop, rice and mushroom casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook dry rice until golden brown.
Pour into 2-quart casserole or roaster.
Cook in same skillet oleo, mushrooms, onion and celery until onion and celery are tender or transparent.
Add water, bouillon cubes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over rice.
Stir to mix.
Place chops on top.
Put layer of tomatoes on chops.
Cover.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add onion and cook until tender. Add flour, whisk.
Cook 1 minute on low heat, stirring.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Cook on medium heat, stirring until thickened. Add cheese and seasonings, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add vegetables and parsley.
Reduce heat and cook until heated.
Do not boil.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of salt with 2 quarts of water.
Soak rind overnight; drain.
Rinse with clear water and drain.
Cook in fresh water until tender (about 10 minutes).
Drain thoroughly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash with onion in small amount of water until squash is tender.
Drain squash.
Mix in egg, margarine, salt and pepper.
Put in baking dish.
Top
with cheese slices and crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon herb pasta
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss thoroughly.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream shortening. Add sugar gradually. Add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each one. Slowly add flour and salt. Mix well. Add flavorings and pineapple (drained). Mix well. Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt pan. Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: In a 3-quart deep casserole dish, mix soup, gravy, vegetables, tarragon and chicken together.
Top with pie crust.
Trim edges with knife.
With a fork, poke pie crust dough twice for steam holes.
Spread tablespoon of milk on top of crust to help it brown.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden. Serves 4.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and take off bone.
Cook spaghetti according to direction and drain.
Add cheese to spaghetti and melt cheese. Mix chicken and all other ingredients to spaghetti mixtures.
Put in casserole dish and bake on low temperature until onions and pepper are tender.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Peel, core and chop enough apples to fill crock-pot heaping full (apples will shrink as they cook).
Sprinkle with other ingredients.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil rotelle noodles and drain.
In large bowl, add broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, onion, tomato, salt, pepper, Zesty Italian salad dressing and noodles.
Stir and mix well.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Saute sesame seed in butter; add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over diced chicken; toss lightly.
Serves 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salty water. Pick off bones. Add cream of chicken soup and sour cream. Mix together real good. Put in layers in pan as you would banana pudding. Then the crackers and oleo mixed together, sprinkled over top. Place in oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, cocoa and nuts. Beat and pour into a 9-inch square pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the first 3 ingredients. remove from heat and add remaining ingredients while mixture is still hot. Beat in 2 eggs, 1/2 cup sour cream 1 tsp. baking soda. Do not use mixer, use wooden spoon. Pour batter into greased sheet cake pan. Batter will be thin. Bake in 375 degrees oven for 20-22 minutes until cake is done.

title: three-minute coconut pie
directions: Combine melted oleo, sugar, coconut, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let set at least 1 hour after baking before serving.

title: cream of lima bean and tomato soup
directions: Put lima beans, water and tomatoes in a saucepan, cover and cook until beans are soft.
Press the mixture through a sieve. Melt butter in saucepan and add flour, mixing well.
Add milk and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add slowly to the lima bean mixture and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and paprika together.
Add corn and beaten egg yolks; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fry in hot, deep fat (365°) until browned.
Drain on paper towels. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Mix by hand with sour cream and soups.
Spread into casserole dish and top with crackers.
Melt butter and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Can be frozen until needed.
Delicious with salad, green peas and rice or potatoes.

title: smooth and creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding, sugar and milk.
Beat slowly at low speed for 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cake (9 x 13).
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: tomato toss
directions: Chop up all the vegetables and mix together.
Dump Italian dressing over vegetables and mix together.
Chill and serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
Form into small balls and dip tops in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: brownies(chocolate squares)
directions: * If you use plain flour use slight.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Rinse
broccoli.
Trim stem ends.
Remove flowerets and steam for
minutes.
(Can microwave for 8 minutes on High and
let stand for 4 minutes, until broccoli is fork tender.) Set
broccoli aside.
In
a
large saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until transparent.	Blend in flour,
salt
and pepper.
Stir
constantly, about 2 minutes. Gradually add broth, then broccoli; stir frequently.
Transfer mixture
to
blender
or food processor in batches and pureed. Then	return	to saucepan and add milk or cream.
Heat through until	warm.
Serve sprinkled with grated cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: german potato salad
directions: Brown bacon in skillet; crumble. Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon drippings. Saute onions in drippings. Blend together soup, water, vinegar, sugar and pepper. Add bacon and onions; mix well. Add potatoes and parsley; mix well. Pour into slow cooker. Cover. Cook on low 4 hours. Serve hot or warm.

title: california newspaper white chili
directions: Saute onions in oil until they turn translucent.
Add garlic, chilies, and spices; saute 2 minutes.
Add stock and drained beans and cook until the beans are done (usually about 2 hours).
While the beans are cooking, cut the chicken into 3/4 inch cubes.
When the beans are done, add the chicken.
(You can also use the meat from a store-bought roasted chicken to save some time.)
Cook 5 to 10 minutes until the chicken is done.
Add 2 c. of cheese and stir until completely melted.
Use additional cheese for garnish. Serves 8.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, then add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes. While still hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: white swedish cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and cool.
Sift flour with soda and salt. Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg, then chocolate.
Stir vanilla into milk.
Add alternately wet and dry ingredients, beating after each addition until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, just until done (or they get too dry).
Cool and frost.

title: sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in a bowl.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the oleo, water, oil and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar mix.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Use a 17 x 11 1/2-inch pan.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done. Remove bones and tear meat into bite-size pieces. In a mixing bowl, combine chicken with sour cream, mushroom and chicken soups and poppy seeds. Spoon into a greased baking dish. Top with broken Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: orange gumdrop cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Cream butter and 2 cups sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Finely chop dates, gumdrops and pecans and dust them with a little flour.
Add to creamed mixture along with coconut and orange rind.
Dissolve soda in the buttermilk and add with the rest of flour to batter, fruit and nut mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in large greased and floured tube pan for 2 hours.

title: delicious fruit dip
directions: Combine marshmallow cream and cream cheese; mix until well blended.
The cream cheese should be softened.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease quiche dish.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread in bottom of dish.
Beat in milk, baking mix and and eggs until smooth (about 1 minute by hand).
Pour over meat mixture in dish.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Take out and layer sliced tomato over top, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let set 5 minutes before cutting. Serves 6.

title: jalapeno chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts until thin, but not torn.
Cover each breast with Mozzarella cheese and 1 whole jalapeno pepper.
Roll the combination and hold with toothpick.
Repeat with remaining breasts.
Place in ungreased baking dish and cover with can of cream of chicken soup (undiluted).
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour.

title: minestrone
directions: In a crock-pot, combine beef, water, tomatoes, bouillon, onion, parsley, salt, thyme and pepper.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours or until meat is tender.
Add zucchini, cabbage, beans and macaroni.
Cook on high, covered, 30 to 45 minutes until the vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle individual servings with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 the mixture into tube pan.
Mix cinnamon, brown sugar and pecans and sprinkle 1/2 over mixture of batter in pan.
Add rest of cake mixture.
Now add rest of cinnamon mixture.
Take a knife and circle through entire mixture except very bottom.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: royal meringue dessert
directions: In large bowl, let egg whites warm to room temperature (1 hour).
Section oranges.
Hold fruit over bowl; with sharp knife, remove peel and white membrane by cutting around in a spiral.
Cut on each side of dividing membrane, lift out sections.
Refrigerate.

title: low calorie dip
directions: In food processor, chop vegetables and olives finely.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: grape velvet ice cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine fruit juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add whipping cream; stir until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Freeze for 3 to 4 hours or until almost firm.

title: my mom's apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples and place in 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix together next 4 ingredients. Add egg and blend until mealy. Sprinkle on top of apples. Melt margarine and add cinnamon and vanilla. Pour over top of egg mixture. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a bowl.
Cut biscuits into fourths and roll in sugar mixture until completely covered.
Place pieces into ungreased Bundt cake pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 1/4 sticks margarine in saucepan.
Heat to a boil.
Pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not cut.
Pull pieces off and eat.

title: quick to fix quesadilla
directions: In heavy foil, stack tortillas with cheese and peppers in between, ending with cheese and peppers on top; cover.
Place on coals of campfire or on grill rack above medium coals.
Cook about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut into 6 or 8 wedges. Serve with salsa and sour cream.
This recipe can be converted to oven or microwave.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Lightly grease an 8-inch square dish and set aside.
Place sugar and cocoa in a medium size glass bowl.
Stir to combine. Add milk and margarine.
Do not stir.
Heat, uncovered, on full power for 2 minutes. After cooking, stir just to combine ingredients. Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Pour into the prepared dish and refrigerate for 1 hour before cutting.

title: so-easy pork chop casserole
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of casserole.
Pour green beans and liquid over potatoes.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican fondue
directions: In top of double boiler, fondue pot or in microwave oven, melt cheese.
Add chunky taco sauce, chiles and taco seasoning mix; blend well.
Let flavors blend at least 1/2 hour before serving. Makes about 1 quart fondue.
Serve hot with bread cubes or corn chips.
Very good!!

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix juices with water.
Pour over orange sherbet or ice cubes and maraschino cherries.
Add the ginger ale.
Chill.

title: old-fashioned virginia corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; gradually add milk, eggs, salt and butter.
Add to canned corn.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put all the dry ingredients in 9 x 13-inch cake pan and mix thoroughly with a fork.
Make 3 indentations in them and put oil in one, vanilla in another and vinegar in the other.
Add water and mix well with fork or whisk.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes. When cool, frost with Quick and Easy Chocolate Frosting.

title: pickling recipe
directions: Bring mixture to a boil.
Cool before pouring on cabbage to make kraut.
You can make pickled beans or corn; cook until tender.
No seasoning on these.

title: banana nut bread(the best)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add bananas and milk; mix well with mixer.
Add eggs and blend.
Mix together and add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: scottish shortbread fingers
directions: Sift; sieve flour, ground rice and sugar into a mixing bowl. Add butter; knead and squeeze into the dry ingredients using one hand only until mixture is combined to a smooth, stiff dough. Roll dough out on a lightly floured surface to a
6 x 10-inch oblong, using gently even pressure with a lightly floured rolling pin.
Cut down center of oblong, trim edges and cut across into fingers.
Place fingers on greased baking tray.
Prick well with fork and place in refrigerator to rest for at least 30 minutes. Bake in a slow oven (300° to 325°) for 15 to 20 minutes until light golden.
Allow to set on baking trays before removing to a wire cooling tray.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 16 to 18 fingers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: banana-berry drink
directions: Remove the peel from the banana. Use the table knife to cut the banana into chunks.

title: mama's friday night special
directions: Come home Friday night.
Peel off panty hose and everything that binds, pinches, cinches, flattens, lifts and tightens.
Put on something loose and comfortable.
Herd kids and husband into car.
Drive to J.D.'s Truck Stop.
Eat!
Get Dad to pay!

title: pan coating
directions: Mix and store in covered container.
Keep at room temperature. (Use for pans that need to be greased in baking items.)

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Coarsely slice cabbage in deep, greased baking dish.
Slightly brown meat and onions; salt and pepper to taste.
Add uncooked rice into meat mixture and stir.
Pour this over cabbage.
Mix together tomatoes and catsup.
Pour over meat, onions and cabbage (do not stir).
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until cabbage is tender.

title: filled mushroom caps
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems from caps.
Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Add sour cream and horseradish. Spoon mixture into caps to fill.
Place on broiler pan.
Broil until top of mushrooms turn light brown.

title: frozen green tomatoes
directions: Mix the flour, salt, pepper and seasoning together. Shake all water off chicken. Dip in the dry mix and fry until done, about 30 minutes.
Place in a clean, dry hot canning jar. Cover with the hot oil or shortening you fried the chicken in and seal.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Shred zucchini.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Mix with next 7 ingredients; shape into 2 patties.
Cook until browned on both sides.

title: taco ring
directions: Add seasoning packet to beef and simmer.
Arrange crescents in a circle on outer 2 inches of a baking stone, points to outside of circle.
Combine meat, beans and cheese and spread on crescent rolls.
Fold in triangles and tuck under.
Cut and serve warm. V-cut green pepper, fill with salsa and place in middle of open circle.
Place chopped onions, lettuce, tomatoes and sliced olives around pepper.
Decorate ring with sour cream.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla with flour mixture.
Add nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased pan. Cook at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: quick and easy peanut brittle
directions: Line 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with foil.
Generously butter foil.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in deep, 2-quart glass dish. Cook on High for 5 minutes in microwave.
Stir in 2 tablespoons butter, peanuts and vanilla with wooden spoon.
Cook on High 5 minutes.
Take out of microwave and stir in baking soda.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook rice
very slowly in plenty of boiling water until tender; add salt.
Rinse
or
3 times in cold water.
Drain well.
Add	pineapple,
cherries,
cherry juice, marshmallows, sugar and topping.	Chill well in refrigerator.

title: gram panter's candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes or use canned.
Combine butter, orange rind, marmalade, salt and brown sugar in frypan for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add sweet potatoes; cook uncovered (with control at 200 in electric skillet), basting and stirring for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are well glazed.

title: peanut butter cookies(easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Put raisins in pan.
Cover with water; bring to a boil.
Let set 15 minutes; drain.
Beat egg yolks with a fork.
Add sugar, vinegar, melted butter, nuts and raisins.
Beat egg whites just until foamy.
Fold in mixture and pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes longer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup and vanilla.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Mix in the pecans.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let cool before slicing.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Beat the eggs slightly. Mix together the flour and sugar. Add to eggs. Add margarine, milk, coconut and vanilla. Coat pie plate with butter. Pour in ingredients and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: stewed green beans
directions: String the beans.
Cut.
Cook with water to cover.
Saute onion in heated oil.
Add can of tomatoes and tomato
sauce and cook slowly, about half hour.
Add to green beans.
Season with salt, pepper and the parsley (minced).
Cook until done.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with the rest of ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Great with veggies, chips and crackers.

title: "paximathakia" - sweet rusks
directions: Cream butter; add oil and beat.
Add sugar and beat again.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add brandy and vanilla, then add flour with the other dry ingredients.
Add sufficient flour to make a soft dough.
You may add 1/2 cup chopped pecans, which have been dredged in flour.
Shape into 6 loaves.
Do 3 loaves on one cookie sheet. Roll and pat the loaves out about the length of the cookie sheet.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the sugar, cocoa and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour gradually.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in greased sheet pan, 13 x 9-inches, for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
When cake is done, immediately spread Marshmallow Creme over top.
(I remove top from Marshmallow Creme and microwave for 30 to 40 seconds before spreading on top.
It will make it spread easier.)
Let cool before frosting.

title: german lentil soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepot over low heat, cook bacon until lightly browned; push to side of Dutch oven.
Add onions, carrots and celery; over medium heat, cook until vegetables are tender.
Add ham bone, lentils, bay leaf, water, pepper, thyme and 1 teaspoon salt; over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour or until lentils are tender.
Discard bay leaf.

title: chocolate cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°; let cool.
Mix with mixer the Cool Whip, powdered sugar and softened cream cheese.
Spread on top of baked crust.
Mix the pudding as directed on package; spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with additional Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mother's strawberry salad
directions: Pour strawberries and pineapple together and drain well; set aside.
Whip cream until stiff peaks form, add marshmallows, pecans and rest of ingredients.
Mix well, but do not stir.
Chill before serving.

title: delicious chocolate pie
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts. Press into pie pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: skillet beef and noodles
directions: Saute beef lightly in skillet, add onion and pepper before meat is too brown.
Cook noodles in water with bouillon cubes.
Do Not Drain Noodles.
Pour into skillet with all other ingredients. Bring to boil, reduce heat and cook until desired consistency.

title: cherry tomato appetizers
directions: Cut a thin slice from stem end of each tomato.
Remove pulp and invert on paper towel to drain.
Combine all other ingredients to form a consistency.
Stuff tomatoes using a small spoon. Garnish with parsley.
Make ahead and chill.
Yields 40.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Mix pineapple and Jell-O together in a saucepan and bring to a full boil.
Cool.
Add buttermilk to mixture and refrigerate until it begins to set.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Chill.
Serve with a topping of equal parts or sour cream and mayonnaise.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Combine salad fruits and marshmallows.
Make sauce in top of double boiler, cooking eggs, vinegar and sugar until thick.
When cool, add butter.
When cold fold in whipped cream.
Add fruit and refrigerate 24 hours.
Will serve 10 amply.
Can be frozen in refrigerator tray.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add bananas and 1/3 cup sour milk and beat well.	Beat in flour mixture with an additional 1/3 cup sour milk.
Grease and flour or place a circle of wax paper into two 9-inch round pans, greasing and flouring sides of pans.
Put equal amount of batter in pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until tested done with toothpick.

title: pesto oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°F.
Line pan with aluminum foil.

title: spamcakes(breakfast)
directions: Preparation: 5 minutes.
Cooking Time: 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in ungreased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with tomato gravy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: curried cherries
directions: In a small saucepan, combine lime juice and pulp, honey, ginger, cinnamon, curry and bay leaves.
Heat over low heat until honey becomes liquid, then stir well to combine.
Rinse and pit cherries. Add them, still wet, to the saucepan.
Simmer over medium heat, stirring frequently, until cherries are slightly wilted and are well coated with curry mixture, about 5 minutes. Serve warm with roasted meat or poultry.

title: best pickled beets
directions: Combine beets, beet juice, vinegar and Equal
in medium bowl. Cover tightly
Chill at least 8 hours before serving.
Drain and serve.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown
meat
and
onion.
Add
sauce,
garlic
salt and oregano.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella. Mix eggs,
milk, oil and flour.
Pour over ingredients in pan. Sprinkle
with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: fruit slush salad
directions: Mix concentrated lemonade, orange juice and water together in large bowl.
Add frozen berries, cutting strawberries in quarters or smaller.
Add pineapple with its juice.
Cut peaches into bite-size bits and add fruit with its juice.
Mix well with wooden spoon.
Divide this mixture into 5 ounce paper cups; place in freezer.
Remove (only number of servings needed) 1/2 to 3/4 hour before serving to allow "slush" effect.

title: minted butter
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a small saucepan over low heat. Stir in mint.
Cook on carrots, peas and broiled tomatoes.
Yield: 1/4 cup.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Use crescent rolls; divide into 8 rectangles. Roll out thin. Use mixer and blend cream cheese, butter and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put mixture (small amount) on each rectangle. Fold over and seal. Can dampen edges with water to make a good seal. Brush rectangles with melted butter and roll in crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
